v8
V8 is Googleâ€™s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

95void SourceCodeCache::Initialize(Isolate* isolate, bool create_heap_objects) {
96 cache_ = create_heap_objects ? ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).empty_fixed_array()
97 : Tagged<FixedArray>();
98}
99
100void SourceCodeCache::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) {
101 v->VisitRootPointer(Root::kExtensions, nullptr, FullObjectSlot(&cache_));
102}
103
104bool SourceCodeCache::Lookup(Isolate* isolate, base::Vector<const char> name,
105 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo>* handle) {
106 for (int i = 0; i < cache_->length(); i += 2) {
107 Tagged<SeqOneByteString> str = Cast<SeqOneByteString>(cache_->get(i));
108 if (str->IsOneByteEqualTo(name)) {
109 *handle =
110 direct_handle(Cast<SharedFunctionInfo>(cache_->get(i + 1)), isolate);
111 return true;
112 }
113 }
114 return false;
115}
116
117void SourceCodeCache::Add(Isolate* isolate, base::Vector<const char> name,
118 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared) {
119 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
120 HandleScope scope(isolate);
121 int length = cache_->length();
122 DirectHandle<FixedArray> new_array =
123 factory->NewFixedArray(length + 2, AllocationType::kOld);
124 FixedArray::CopyElements(isolate, *new_array, 0, cache_, 0, cache_->length());
125 cache_ = *new_array;
126 DirectHandle<String> str =
127 factory
128 ->NewStringFromOneByte(base::Vector<const uint8_t>::cast(name),
129 AllocationType::kOld)
130 .ToHandleChecked();
131 DCHECK(!str.is_null());
132 cache_->set(length, *str);
133 cache_->set(length + 1, *shared);
134 Cast<Script>(shared->script())->set_type(type_);
135}

137Bootstrapper::Bootstrapper(Isolate* isolate)
138 : isolate_(isolate),
139 nesting_(0),
140 extensions_cache_(Script::Type::kExtension) {}
141
142void Bootstrapper::Initialize(bool create_heap_objects) {
143 extensions_cache_.Initialize(isolate_, create_heap_objects);
144}
145
146static const char* GCFunctionName() {
147 bool flag_given =
148 v8_flags.expose_gc_as != nullptr && strlen(v8_flags.expose_gc_as) != 0;
149 return flag_given ? v8_flags.expose_gc_as : "gc";
150}
151
152static bool isValidCpuTraceMarkFunctionName() {
153 return v8_flags.expose_cputracemark_as != nullptr &&
154 strlen(v8_flags.expose_cputracemark_as) != 0;
155}
156
157void Bootstrapper::InitializeOncePerProcess() {
158 v8::RegisterExtension(std::make_unique<GCExtension>(GCFunctionName()));
159#ifdef V8_FUZZILLI
160 v8::RegisterExtension(std::make_unique<FuzzilliExtension>("fuzzilli"));
161#endif
162 v8::RegisterExtension(std::make_unique<ExternalizeStringExtension>());
163 v8::RegisterExtension(std::make_unique<StatisticsExtension>());
164 v8::RegisterExtension(std::make_unique<TriggerFailureExtension>());
165 v8::RegisterExtension(std::make_unique<IgnitionStatisticsExtension>());
166 if (isValidCpuTraceMarkFunctionName()) {
167 v8::RegisterExtension(std::make_unique<CpuTraceMarkExtension>(
168 v8_flags.expose_cputracemark_as));
169 }
170#ifdef ENABLE_VTUNE_TRACEMARK
171 v8::RegisterExtension(
172 std::make_unique<VTuneDomainSupportExtension>("vtunedomainmark"));
173#endif // ENABLE_VTUNE_TRACEMARK
174}
175
176void Bootstrapper::TearDown() {
177 extensions_cache_.Initialize(isolate_, false); // Yes, symmetrical
178}

180class Genesis {
181 public:
182 Genesis(Isolate* isolate, MaybeDirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> maybe_global_proxy,
183 v8::Local<v8::ObjectTemplate> global_proxy_template,
184 size_t context_snapshot_index,
185 DeserializeEmbedderFieldsCallback embedder_fields_deserializer,
186 v8::MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue);
187 Genesis(Isolate* isolate, MaybeDirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> maybe_global_proxy,
188 v8::Local<v8::ObjectTemplate> global_proxy_template);
189 ~Genesis() = default;
190
191 Isolate* isolate() const { return isolate_; }
192 Factory* factory() const { return isolate_->factory(); }
193 Builtins* builtins() const { return isolate_->builtins(); }
194 Heap* heap() const { return isolate_->heap(); }
195
196 DirectHandle<NativeContext> result() { return result_; }
197
198 DirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> global_proxy() { return global_proxy_; }
199
200 private:
201 DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context() { return native_context_; }
202
203 // Creates some basic objects. Used for creating a context from scratch.
204 void CreateRoots();
205 // Creates the empty function. Used for creating a context from scratch.
206 Handle<JSFunction> CreateEmptyFunction();
207 // Returns the %ThrowTypeError% intrinsic function.
208 // See ES#sec-%throwtypeerror% for details.
209 DirectHandle<JSFunction> GetThrowTypeErrorIntrinsic();

211 void CreateSloppyModeFunctionMaps(DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty);
212 void CreateStrictModeFunctionMaps(DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty);
213 void CreateObjectFunction(DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty);
214 void CreateIteratorMaps(DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty);

216 void CreateAsyncFunctionMaps(DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty);
217 void CreateJSProxyMaps();
218
219 // Make the "arguments" and "caller" properties throw a TypeError on access.
220 void AddRestrictedFunctionProperties(DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty);
221
222 // Creates the global objects using the global proxy and the template passed
223 // in through the API. We call this regardless of whether we are building a
224 // context from scratch or using a deserialized one from the context snapshot
225 // but in the latter case we don't use the objects it produces directly, as
226 // we have to use the deserialized ones that are linked together with the
227 // rest of the context snapshot. At the end we link the global proxy and the
228 // context to each other.
229 Handle<JSGlobalObject> CreateNewGlobals(
230 v8::Local<v8::ObjectTemplate> global_proxy_template,
231 DirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> global_proxy);
232 // Similarly, we want to use the global that has been created by the templates
233 // passed through the API. The global from the snapshot is detached from the
234 // other objects in the snapshot.
235 void HookUpGlobalObject(DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> global_object);
236 // Hooks the given global proxy into the context in the case we do not
237 // replace the global object from the deserialized native context.
238 void HookUpGlobalProxy(DirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> global_proxy);
239 // The native context has a ScriptContextTable that store declarative bindings
240 // made in script scopes. Add a "this" binding to that table pointing to the
241 // global proxy.
242 void InstallGlobalThisBinding();
243 // New context initialization. Used for creating a context from scratch.
244 void InitializeGlobal(DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> global_object,
245 DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty_function);
246 void InitializeExperimentalGlobal();
247 void InitializeIteratorFunctions();
248 void InitializeCallSiteBuiltins();
249 void InitializeConsole(DirectHandle<JSObject> extras_binding);

342void Bootstrapper::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) {
343 extensions_cache_.Iterate(v);
344 v->Synchronize(VisitorSynchronization::kExtensions);
345}
346
347DirectHandle<NativeContext> Bootstrapper::CreateEnvironment(
348 MaybeDirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> maybe_global_proxy,
349 v8::Local<v8::ObjectTemplate> global_proxy_template,
350 v8::ExtensionConfiguration* extensions, size_t context_snapshot_index,
351 DeserializeEmbedderFieldsCallback embedder_fields_deserializer,
352 v8::MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue) {
353 HandleScope scope(isolate_);
354 DirectHandle<NativeContext> env;
355 {
356 Genesis genesis(isolate_, maybe_global_proxy, global_proxy_template,
357 context_snapshot_index, embedder_fields_deserializer,
358 microtask_queue);
359 env = genesis.result();
360 if (env.is_null() || !InstallExtensions(env, extensions)) {
361 return {};
362 }
363 }
364 LogAllMaps();
365 isolate_->heap()->NotifyBootstrapComplete();
366 return scope.CloseAndEscape(env);
367}
368
369DirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> Bootstrapper::NewRemoteContext(
370 MaybeDirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> maybe_global_proxy,
371 v8::Local<v8::ObjectTemplate> global_proxy_template) {
372 HandleScope scope(isolate_);
373 DirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> global_proxy;
374 {
375 Genesis genesis(isolate_, maybe_global_proxy, global_proxy_template);
376 global_proxy = genesis.global_proxy();
377 if (global_proxy.is_null()) return {};
378 }
379 LogAllMaps();
380 return scope.CloseAndEscape(global_proxy);
381}
382
383void Bootstrapper::LogAllMaps() {
384 if (!v8_flags.log_maps || isolate_->initialized_from_snapshot()) return;
385 // Log all created Map objects that are on the heap. For snapshots the Map
386 // logging happens during deserialization in order to avoid printing Maps
387 // multiple times during partial deserialization.
388 LOG(isolate_, LogAllMaps());
389}

393#ifdef DEBUG
394bool IsFunctionMapOrSpecialBuiltin(DirectHandle<Map> map, Builtin builtin,
395 DirectHandle<Context> context) {
396 // During bootstrapping some of these maps could be not created yet.
397 return ((*map == context->get(Context::STRICT_FUNCTION_MAP_INDEX)) ||
398 (*map == context->get(
399 Context::STRICT_FUNCTION_WITHOUT_PROTOTYPE_MAP_INDEX)) ||
400 (*map ==
401 context->get(
402 Context::STRICT_FUNCTION_WITH_READONLY_PROTOTYPE_MAP_INDEX)) ||
403 // Check if it's a creation of an empty or Proxy function during
404 // bootstrapping.
405 (builtin == Builtin::kEmptyFunction ||
406 builtin == Builtin::kProxyConstructor));
407}
408#endif // DEBUG
409
410Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> CreateSharedFunctionInfoForBuiltin(
411 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<String> name, Builtin builtin, int len,
412 AdaptArguments adapt) {
413 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> info =
414 isolate->factory()->NewSharedFunctionInfoForBuiltin(name, builtin, len,
415 adapt);
416 info->set_language_mode(LanguageMode::kStrict);
417
418#ifdef DEBUG
419 Tagged<Code> code = info->GetCode(isolate);
420 if (code->parameter_count() != kDontAdaptArgumentsSentinel) {
421 DCHECK_EQ(info->internal_formal_parameter_count_with_receiver(),
422 code->parameter_count());
423 }
424#endif
425
426 return info;
427}
428
429V8_NOINLINE Handle<JSFunction> CreateFunctionForBuiltin(
430 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<String> name, DirectHandle<Map> map,
431 Builtin builtin, int len, AdaptArguments adapt) {
432 DirectHandle<NativeContext> context(isolate->native_context());
433 DCHECK(IsFunctionMapOrSpecialBuiltin(map, builtin, context));
434
435 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> info =
436 CreateSharedFunctionInfoForBuiltin(isolate, name, builtin, len, adapt);
437
438 return Factory::JSFunctionBuilder{isolate, info, context}
439 .set_map(map)
440 .Build();
441}
442
443V8_NOINLINE Handle<JSFunction> CreateFunctionForBuiltinWithPrototype(
444 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<String> name, Builtin builtin,
445 DirectHandle<UnionOf<JSPrototype, Hole>> prototype, InstanceType type,
446 int instance_size, int inobject_properties,
447 MutableMode prototype_mutability, int len, AdaptArguments adapt) {
448 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
449 DirectHandle<NativeContext> context(isolate->native_context());
450 DirectHandle<Map> map =
451 prototype_mutability == MUTABLE
452 ? isolate->strict_function_map()
453 : isolate->strict_function_with_readonly_prototype_map();
454 DCHECK(IsFunctionMapOrSpecialBuiltin(map, builtin, context));
455
456 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> info =
457 CreateSharedFunctionInfoForBuiltin(isolate, name, builtin, len, adapt);
458 info->set_expected_nof_properties(inobject_properties);
459
460 Handle<JSFunction> result =
461 Factory::JSFunctionBuilder{isolate, info, context}.set_map(map).Build();
462
463 ElementsKind elements_kind;
464 switch (type) {
465 case JS_ARRAY_TYPE:
466 elements_kind = PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS;
467 break;
468 case JS_ARGUMENTS_OBJECT_TYPE:
469 elements_kind = PACKED_ELEMENTS;
470 break;
471 default:
472 elements_kind = TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND;
473 break;
474 }
475 DirectHandle<Map> initial_map = factory->NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
476 type, instance_size, elements_kind, inobject_properties);
477 initial_map->SetConstructor(*result);
478 if (type == JS_FUNCTION_TYPE) {
479 DCHECK_EQ(instance_size, JSFunction::kSizeWithPrototype);
480 // Since we are creating an initial map for JSFunction objects with
481 // prototype slot, set the respective bit.
482 initial_map->set_has_prototype_slot(true);
483 }
484 // TODO(littledan): Why do we have this is_generator test when
485 // NewFunctionPrototype already handles finding an appropriately
486 // shared prototype?
487 if (!IsResumableFunction(info->kind()) && IsTheHole(*prototype, isolate)) {
488 prototype = factory->NewFunctionPrototype(result);
489 }
490 JSFunction::SetInitialMap(isolate, result, initial_map,
491 Cast<JSPrototype>(prototype));
492
493 return result;
494}
495
496V8_NOINLINE Handle<JSFunction> CreateFunctionForBuiltinWithoutPrototype(
497 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<String> name, Builtin builtin, int len,
498 AdaptArguments adapt) {
499 DirectHandle<NativeContext> context(isolate->native_context());
500 DirectHandle<Map> map = isolate->strict_function_without_prototype_map();
501 DCHECK(IsFunctionMapOrSpecialBuiltin(map, builtin, context));
502
503 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> info =
504 CreateSharedFunctionInfoForBuiltin(isolate, name, builtin, len, adapt);
505
506 return Factory::JSFunctionBuilder{isolate, info, context}
507 .set_map(map)
508 .Build();
509}
510
511V8_NOINLINE Handle<JSFunction> CreateFunction(
512 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<String> name, InstanceType type,
513 int instance_size, int inobject_properties,
514 DirectHandle<UnionOf<JSPrototype, Hole>> prototype, Builtin builtin,
515 int len, AdaptArguments adapt) {
516 DCHECK(Builtins::HasJSLinkage(builtin));
517
518 Handle<JSFunction> result = CreateFunctionForBuiltinWithPrototype(
519 isolate, name, builtin, prototype, type, instance_size,
520 inobject_properties, IMMUTABLE, len, adapt);
521
522 // Make the JSFunction's prototype object fast.
523 JSObject::MakePrototypesFast(direct_handle(result->prototype(), isolate),
524 kStartAtReceiver, isolate);
525
526 // Make the resulting JSFunction object fast.
527 JSObject::MakePrototypesFast(result, kStartAtReceiver, isolate);
528 result->shared()->set_native(true);
529 return result;
530}
531
532V8_NOINLINE Handle<JSFunction> CreateFunction(
533 Isolate* isolate, const char* name, InstanceType type, int instance_size,
534 int inobject_properties, DirectHandle<UnionOf<JSPrototype, Hole>> prototype,
535 Builtin builtin, int len, AdaptArguments adapt) {
536 return CreateFunction(
537 isolate, isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String(name), type,
538 instance_size, inobject_properties, prototype, builtin, len, adapt);
539}

541V8_NOINLINE Handle<JSFunction> InstallFunction(
542 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> target, DirectHandle<String> name,
543 InstanceType type, int instance_size, int inobject_properties,
544 DirectHandle<UnionOf<JSPrototype, Hole>> prototype, Builtin call, int len,
545 AdaptArguments adapt) {
546 DCHECK(Builtins::HasJSLinkage(call));
547 Handle<JSFunction> function =
548 CreateFunction(isolate, name, type, instance_size, inobject_properties,
549 prototype, call, len, adapt);
550 JSObject::AddProperty(isolate, target, name, function, DONT_ENUM);
551 return function;
552}
553
554V8_NOINLINE Handle<JSFunction> InstallFunction(
555 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> target, const char* name,
556 InstanceType type, int instance_size, int inobject_properties,
557 DirectHandle<UnionOf<JSPrototype, Hole>> prototype, Builtin call, int len,
558 AdaptArguments adapt) {
559 return InstallFunction(
560 isolate, target, isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String(name), type,
561 instance_size, inobject_properties, prototype, call, len, adapt);
562}
563
564// This sets a constructor instance type on the constructor map which will be
565// used in IsXxxConstructor() predicates. Having such predicates helps figuring
566// out if a protector cell should be invalidated. If there are no protector
567// cell checks required for constructor, this function must not be used.
568// Note, this function doesn't create a copy of the constructor's map. So it's
569// better to set constructor instance type after all the properties are added
570// to the constructor and thus the map is already guaranteed to be unique.
571V8_NOINLINE void SetConstructorInstanceType(
572 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSFunction> constructor,
573 InstanceType constructor_type) {
574 DCHECK(InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSFunction(constructor_type));
575 DCHECK_NE(constructor_type, JS_FUNCTION_TYPE);
576
577 Tagged<Map> map = constructor->map();
578
579 // Check we don't accidentally change one of the existing maps.
580 DCHECK_NE(map, *isolate->strict_function_map());
581 DCHECK_NE(map, *isolate->strict_function_with_readonly_prototype_map());
582 // Constructor function map is always a root map, and thus we don't have to
583 // deal with updating the whole transition tree.
584 DCHECK(IsUndefined(map->GetBackPointer(), isolate));
585 DCHECK_EQ(JS_FUNCTION_TYPE, map->instance_type());
586
587 map->set_instance_type(constructor_type);
588}
589
590V8_NOINLINE Handle<JSFunction> SimpleCreateFunction(Isolate* isolate,
591 DirectHandle<String> name,
592 Builtin call, int len,
593 AdaptArguments adapt) {
594 DCHECK(Builtins::HasJSLinkage(call));
595 name = String::Flatten(isolate, name, AllocationType::kOld);
596 Handle<JSFunction> fun =
597 CreateFunctionForBuiltinWithoutPrototype(isolate, name, call, len, adapt);
598 // Make the resulting JSFunction object fast.
599 JSObject::MakePrototypesFast(fun, kStartAtReceiver, isolate);
600 fun->shared()->set_native(true);
601 return fun;
602}

604V8_NOINLINE Handle<JSFunction> InstallFunctionWithBuiltinId(
605 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> base, const char* name,
606 Builtin call, int len, AdaptArguments adapt) {
607 DirectHandle<String> internalized_name =
608 isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String(name);
609 Handle<JSFunction> fun =
610 SimpleCreateFunction(isolate, internalized_name, call, len, adapt);
611 JSObject::AddProperty(isolate, base, internalized_name, fun, DONT_ENUM);

615V8_NOINLINE Handle<JSFunction> InstallFunctionAtSymbol(
616 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> base, DirectHandle<Symbol> symbol,
617 const char* symbol_string, Builtin call, int len, AdaptArguments adapt,
618 PropertyAttributes attrs = DONT_ENUM) {

620 isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String(symbol_string);
621 Handle<JSFunction> fun =

623 JSObject::AddProperty(isolate, base, symbol, fun, attrs);

626
627V8_NOINLINE Handle<JSFunction> CreateSharedObjectConstructor(
628 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<String> name, DirectHandle<Map> instance_map,
629 Builtin builtin, int len, AdaptArguments adapt) {
630 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
631 DirectHandle<SharedFunctionInfo> info =
632 factory->NewSharedFunctionInfoForBuiltin(name, builtin, len, adapt);
633 info->set_language_mode(LanguageMode::kStrict);
634 Handle<JSFunction> constructor =
635 Factory::JSFunctionBuilder{isolate, info, isolate->native_context()}
636 .set_map(isolate->strict_function_with_readonly_prototype_map())
637 .Build();
638 constructor->set_prototype_or_initial_map(*instance_map, kReleaseStore);
639
640 JSObject::AddProperty(
641 isolate, constructor, factory->has_instance_symbol(),
642 direct_handle(
643 isolate->native_context()->shared_space_js_object_has_instance(),
644 isolate),
645 static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | DONT_DELETE | READ_ONLY));
646 return constructor;
647}

649V8_NOINLINE void SimpleInstallGetterSetter(Isolate* isolate,
650 DirectHandle<JSObject> base,
651 Handle<Name> name,
652 Builtin call_getter,
653 Builtin call_setter) {
654 DirectHandle<String> getter_name =
655 Name::ToFunctionName(isolate, name, isolate->factory()->get_string())
656 .ToHandleChecked();
657 DirectHandle<JSFunction> getter =
658 SimpleCreateFunction(isolate, getter_name, call_getter, 0, kAdapt);
659
660 DirectHandle<String> setter_name =
661 Name::ToFunctionName(isolate, name, isolate->factory()->set_string())
662 .ToHandleChecked();
663 DirectHandle<JSFunction> setter =
664 SimpleCreateFunction(isolate, setter_name, call_setter, 1, kAdapt);
665
666 JSObject::DefineOwnAccessorIgnoreAttributes(base, name, getter, setter,
667 DONT_ENUM)
668 .Check();
669}
670
671void SimpleInstallGetterSetter(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> base,
672 const char* name, Builtin call_getter,
673 Builtin call_setter) {
674 SimpleInstallGetterSetter(isolate, base,
675 isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String(name),
676 call_getter, call_setter);
677}

679V8_NOINLINE Handle<JSFunction> SimpleInstallGetter(
680 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> base, Handle<Name> name,
681 DirectHandle<Name> property_name, Builtin call, AdaptArguments adapt) {
682 DirectHandle<String> getter_name =
683 Name::ToFunctionName(isolate, name, isolate->factory()->get_string())
684 .ToHandleChecked();
685 Handle<JSFunction> getter =
686 SimpleCreateFunction(isolate, getter_name, call, 0, adapt);
687
688 DirectHandle<Object> setter = isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
689
690 JSObject::DefineOwnAccessorIgnoreAttributes(base, property_name, getter,
691 setter, DONT_ENUM)
692 .Check();
693
694 return getter;
695}

744
745// Create a map for result objects returned from builtins in such a way that
746// it's exactly the same map as the one produced by object literals. E.g.,
747// iterator result objects have the same map as literals in the form `{value,
748// done}`.
749//
750// This way we have better sharing of maps (i.e. less polymorphism) and also
751// make it possible to hit the fast-paths in various builtins (i.e. promises and
752// collections) with user defined iterators.
753template <size_t N>
754Handle<Map> CreateLiteralObjectMapFromCache(
755 Isolate* isolate, const std::array<DirectHandle<Name>, N>& properties) {
756 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
757 DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context = isolate->native_context();
758 Handle<Map> map = factory->ObjectLiteralMapFromCache(native_context, N);
759 for (DirectHandle<Name> name : properties) {
760 map = Map::CopyWithField(isolate, map, name, FieldType::Any(isolate), NONE,
761 PropertyConstness::kConst,
762 Representation::Tagged(), INSERT_TRANSITION)
763 .ToHandleChecked();
764 }
765 return map;
766}
767
768} // namespace
769
770Handle<JSFunction> Genesis::CreateEmptyFunction() {
771 // Allocate the function map first and then patch the prototype later.
772 DirectHandle<Map> empty_function_map =
773 factory()->CreateSloppyFunctionMap(FUNCTION_WITHOUT_PROTOTYPE, {});
774 empty_function_map->set_is_prototype_map(true);
775 DCHECK(!empty_function_map->is_dictionary_map());
776
777 // Allocate the empty function as the prototype for function according to
778 // ES#sec-properties-of-the-function-prototype-object
779 Handle<JSFunction> empty_function = CreateFunctionForBuiltin(
780 isolate(), factory()->empty_string(), empty_function_map,
781 Builtin::kEmptyFunction, 0, kDontAdapt);
782 empty_function_map->SetConstructor(*empty_function);
783 native_context()->set_empty_function(*empty_function);
784
785 // --- E m p t y ---
786 DirectHandle<String> source = factory()->InternalizeString("() {}");
787 DirectHandle<Script> script = factory()->NewScript(source);
788 script->set_type(Script::Type::kNative);
789 DirectHandle<WeakFixedArray> infos = factory()->NewWeakFixedArray(2);
790 script->set_infos(*infos);
791 ReadOnlyRoots roots{isolate()};
792 Tagged<SharedFunctionInfo> sfi = empty_function->shared();
793 sfi->set_raw_scope_info(roots.empty_function_scope_info());
794 sfi->SetScript(isolate(), roots, *script, 1);
795 sfi->UpdateFunctionMapIndex();
796
797 return empty_function;
798}
799
800void Genesis::CreateSloppyModeFunctionMaps(DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty) {
801 Factory* factory = isolate_->factory();
802 DirectHandle<Map> map;
803
804 //
805 // Allocate maps for sloppy functions without prototype.
806 //
807 map = factory->CreateSloppyFunctionMap(FUNCTION_WITHOUT_PROTOTYPE, empty);
808 native_context()->set_sloppy_function_without_prototype_map(*map);
809
810 //
811 // Allocate maps for sloppy functions with readonly prototype.
812 //
813 map =
814 factory->CreateSloppyFunctionMap(FUNCTION_WITH_READONLY_PROTOTYPE, empty);
815 native_context()->set_sloppy_function_with_readonly_prototype_map(*map);
816
817 //
818 // Allocate maps for sloppy functions with writable prototype.
819 //
820 map = factory->CreateSloppyFunctionMap(FUNCTION_WITH_WRITEABLE_PROTOTYPE,
821 empty);
822 native_context()->set_sloppy_function_map(*map);
823
824 map = factory->CreateSloppyFunctionMap(
825 FUNCTION_WITH_NAME_AND_WRITEABLE_PROTOTYPE, empty);
826 native_context()->set_sloppy_function_with_name_map(*map);
827}
828
829DirectHandle<JSFunction> Genesis::GetThrowTypeErrorIntrinsic() {
830 if (!restricted_properties_thrower_.is_null()) {
831 return restricted_properties_thrower_;
832 }
833 DirectHandle<String> name = factory()->empty_string();
834 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function = CreateFunctionForBuiltinWithoutPrototype(
835 isolate(), name, Builtin::kStrictPoisonPillThrower, 0, kAdapt);
836
837 // %ThrowTypeError% must have a name property with an empty string value. Per
838 // spec, ThrowTypeError's name is non-configurable, unlike ordinary functions'
839 // name property. To redefine it to be non-configurable, use
840 // SetOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes.
841 JSObject::SetOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes(
842 function, factory()->name_string(), factory()->empty_string(),
843 static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | DONT_DELETE | READ_ONLY))
844 .Assert();
845
846 // length needs to be non configurable.
847 Handle<Object> value(Smi::FromInt(function->length()), isolate());
848 JSObject::SetOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes(
849 function, factory()->length_string(), value,
850 static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | DONT_DELETE | READ_ONLY))
851 .Assert();
852
853 if (JSObject::PreventExtensions(isolate_, function, kThrowOnError)
854 .IsNothing()) {
855 DCHECK(false);
856 }
857
858 JSObject::MigrateSlowToFast(function, 0, "Bootstrapping");
859
860 restricted_properties_thrower_ = function;
861 return function;
862}
863
864void Genesis::CreateStrictModeFunctionMaps(DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty) {
865 Factory* factory = isolate_->factory();
866 DirectHandle<Map> map;
867
868 //
869 // Allocate maps for strict functions without prototype.
870 //
871 map = factory->CreateStrictFunctionMap(FUNCTION_WITHOUT_PROTOTYPE, empty);
872 native_context()->set_strict_function_without_prototype_map(*map);
873
874 map = factory->CreateStrictFunctionMap(METHOD_WITH_NAME, empty);
875 native_context()->set_method_with_name_map(*map);
876
877 //
878 // Allocate maps for strict functions with writable prototype.
879 //
880 map = factory->CreateStrictFunctionMap(FUNCTION_WITH_WRITEABLE_PROTOTYPE,
881 empty);
882 native_context()->set_strict_function_map(*map);
883
884 map = factory->CreateStrictFunctionMap(
885 FUNCTION_WITH_NAME_AND_WRITEABLE_PROTOTYPE, empty);
886 native_context()->set_strict_function_with_name_map(*map);
887
888 //
889 // Allocate maps for strict functions with readonly prototype.
890 //
891 map =
892 factory->CreateStrictFunctionMap(FUNCTION_WITH_READONLY_PROTOTYPE, empty);
893 native_context()->set_strict_function_with_readonly_prototype_map(*map);
894
895 //
896 // Allocate map for class functions.
897 //
898 map = factory->CreateClassFunctionMap(empty);
899 native_context()->set_class_function_map(*map);
900
901 // Now that the strict mode function map is available, set up the
902 // restricted "arguments" and "caller" getters.
903 AddRestrictedFunctionProperties(empty);
904}
905
906void Genesis::CreateObjectFunction(DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty_function) {
907 Factory* factory = isolate_->factory();
908
909 // --- O b j e c t ---
910 int inobject_properties = JSObject::kInitialGlobalObjectUnusedPropertiesCount;
911 int instance_size = JSObject::kHeaderSize + kTaggedSize * inobject_properties;
912
913 DirectHandle<JSFunction> object_fun =
914 CreateFunction(isolate_, factory->Object_string(), JS_OBJECT_TYPE,
915 instance_size, inobject_properties, factory->null_value(),
916 Builtin::kObjectConstructor, 1, kDontAdapt);
917 native_context()->set_object_function(*object_fun);
918
919 {
920 // Finish setting up Object function's initial map.
921 Tagged<Map> initial_map = object_fun->initial_map();
922 initial_map->set_elements_kind(HOLEY_ELEMENTS);
923 }
924
925 // Allocate a new prototype for the object function.
926 DirectHandle<JSObject> object_function_prototype =
927 factory->NewFunctionPrototype(object_fun);
928
929 {
930 DirectHandle<Map> map = Map::Copy(
931 isolate(), direct_handle(object_function_prototype->map(), isolate()),
932 "EmptyObjectPrototype");
933 map->set_is_prototype_map(true);
934 // Ban re-setting Object.prototype.__proto__ to prevent Proxy security bug
935 map->set_is_immutable_proto(true);
936 object_function_prototype->set_map(isolate(), *map);
937 }
938
939 // Complete setting up empty function.
940 {
941 DirectHandle<Map> empty_function_map(empty_function->map(), isolate_);
942 Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), empty_function_map, object_function_prototype);
943 }
944
945 native_context()->set_initial_object_prototype(*object_function_prototype);
946 JSFunction::SetPrototype(object_fun, object_function_prototype);
947 object_function_prototype->map()->set_instance_type(JS_OBJECT_PROTOTYPE_TYPE);
948 {
949 // Set up slow map for Object.create(null) instances without in-object
950 // properties.
951 DirectHandle<Map> map(object_fun->initial_map(), isolate_);
952 map = Map::CopyInitialMapNormalized(isolate(), map);
953 Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), map, factory->null_value());
954 native_context()->set_slow_object_with_null_prototype_map(*map);
955
956 // Set up slow map for literals with too many properties.
957 map = Map::Copy(isolate(), map, "slow_object_with_object_prototype_map");
958 Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), map, object_function_prototype);
959 native_context()->set_slow_object_with_object_prototype_map(*map);
960 }
961}
962
963namespace {
964
965Handle<Map> CreateNonConstructorMap(Isolate* isolate,
966 DirectHandle<Map> source_map,
967 DirectHandle<JSObject> prototype,
968 const char* reason) {
969 Handle<Map> map = Map::Copy(isolate, source_map, reason);
970 // Ensure the resulting map has prototype slot (it is necessary for storing
971 // inital map even when the prototype property is not required).
972 if (!map->has_prototype_slot()) {
973 // Re-set the unused property fields after changing the instance size.
974 int unused_property_fields = map->UnusedPropertyFields();
975 map->set_instance_size(map->instance_size() + kTaggedSize);
976 // The prototype slot shifts the in-object properties area by one slot.
977 map->SetInObjectPropertiesStartInWords(
978 map->GetInObjectPropertiesStartInWords() + 1);
979 map->set_has_prototype_slot(true);
980 map->SetInObjectUnusedPropertyFields(unused_property_fields);
981 }
982 map->set_is_constructor(false);
983 Map::SetPrototype(isolate, map, prototype);
984 return map;
985}
986
987} // namespace
988
989Handle<JSFunction> SimpleInstallFunction(Isolate* isolate,
990 DirectHandle<JSObject> base,
991 const char* name, Builtin call,
992 int len, AdaptArguments adapt,
993 PropertyAttributes attrs) {
994 // Although function name does not have to be internalized the property name
995 // will be internalized during property addition anyway, so do it here now.
996 DirectHandle<String> internalized_name =
997 isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String(name);
998 Handle<JSFunction> fun =
999 SimpleCreateFunction(isolate, internalized_name, call, len, adapt);
1000 JSObject::AddProperty(isolate, base, internalized_name, fun, attrs);
1001 return fun;
1002}
1003
1004void Genesis::CreateIteratorMaps(DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty) {
1005 // Create iterator-related meta-objects.
1006 DirectHandle<JSObject> iterator_prototype = factory()->NewJSObject(
1007 isolate()->object_function(), AllocationType::kOld);
1008
1009 InstallFunctionAtSymbol(isolate(), iterator_prototype,
1010 factory()->iterator_symbol(), "[Symbol.iterator]",
1011 Builtin::kReturnReceiver, 0, kAdapt);
1012 native_context()->set_initial_iterator_prototype(*iterator_prototype);
1013 CHECK_NE(iterator_prototype->map().ptr(),
1014 isolate_->initial_object_prototype()->map().ptr());
1015 iterator_prototype->map()->set_instance_type(JS_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE);
1016
1017 DirectHandle<JSObject> generator_object_prototype = factory()->NewJSObject(
1018 isolate()->object_function(), AllocationType::kOld);
1019 native_context()->set_initial_generator_prototype(
1020 *generator_object_prototype);
1021 JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate(), generator_object_prototype,
1022 iterator_prototype);
1023 DirectHandle<JSObject> generator_function_prototype = factory()->NewJSObject(
1024 isolate()->object_function(), AllocationType::kOld);
1025 JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate(), generator_function_prototype, empty);
1026
1027 InstallToStringTag(isolate(), generator_function_prototype,
1028 "GeneratorFunction");
1029 JSObject::AddProperty(isolate(), generator_function_prototype,
1030 factory()->prototype_string(),
1031 generator_object_prototype,
1032 static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | READ_ONLY));
1033
1034 JSObject::AddProperty(isolate(), generator_object_prototype,
1035 factory()->constructor_string(),
1036 generator_function_prototype,
1037 static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | READ_ONLY));
1038 InstallToStringTag(isolate(), generator_object_prototype, "Generator");
1039 SimpleInstallFunction(isolate(), generator_object_prototype, "next",
1040 Builtin::kGeneratorPrototypeNext, 1, kDontAdapt);
1041 SimpleInstallFunction(isolate(), generator_object_prototype, "return",
1042 Builtin::kGeneratorPrototypeReturn, 1, kDontAdapt);
1043 SimpleInstallFunction(isolate(), generator_object_prototype, "throw",
1044 Builtin::kGeneratorPrototypeThrow, 1, kDontAdapt);
1045
1046 // Internal version of generator_prototype_next, flagged as non-native such
1047 // that it doesn't show up in Error traces.
1048 DirectHandle<JSFunction> generator_next_internal =
1049 SimpleCreateFunction(isolate(), factory()->next_string(),
1050 Builtin::kGeneratorPrototypeNext, 1, kDontAdapt);
1051 generator_next_internal->shared()->set_native(false);
1052 native_context()->set_generator_next_internal(*generator_next_internal);
1053
1054 // Internal version of async module functions, flagged as non-native such
1055 // that they don't show up in Error traces.
1056 {
1057 DirectHandle<JSFunction> async_module_evaluate_internal =
1058 SimpleCreateFunction(isolate(), factory()->next_string(),
1059 Builtin::kAsyncModuleEvaluate, 1, kDontAdapt);
1060 async_module_evaluate_internal->shared()->set_native(false);
1061 native_context()->set_async_module_evaluate_internal(
1062 *async_module_evaluate_internal);
1063 }
1064
1065 // Create maps for generator functions and their prototypes. Store those
1066 // maps in the native context. The "prototype" property descriptor is
1067 // writable, non-enumerable, and non-configurable (as per ES6 draft
1068 // 04-14-15, section 25.2.4.3).
1069 // Generator functions do not have "caller" or "arguments" accessors.
1070 DirectHandle<Map> map;
1071 map = CreateNonConstructorMap(isolate(), isolate()->strict_function_map(),
1072 generator_function_prototype,
1073 "GeneratorFunction");
1074 native_context()->set_generator_function_map(*map);
1075
1076 map = CreateNonConstructorMap(
1077 isolate(), isolate()->strict_function_with_name_map(),
1078 generator_function_prototype, "GeneratorFunction with name");
1079 native_context()->set_generator_function_with_name_map(*map);
1080
1081 DirectHandle<JSFunction> object_function(native_context()->object_function(),
1082 isolate());
1083 DirectHandle<Map> generator_object_prototype_map = Map::Create(isolate(), 0);
1084 Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), generator_object_prototype_map,
1085 generator_object_prototype);
1086 native_context()->set_generator_object_prototype_map(
1087 *generator_object_prototype_map);
1088}
1089
1090void Genesis::CreateAsyncIteratorMaps(DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty) {
1091 // %AsyncIteratorPrototype%
1092 // proposal-async-iteration/#sec-asynciteratorprototype
1093 DirectHandle<JSObject> async_iterator_prototype = factory()->NewJSObject(
1094 isolate()->object_function(), AllocationType::kOld);
1095
1096 InstallFunctionAtSymbol(
1097 isolate(), async_iterator_prototype, factory()->async_iterator_symbol(),
1098 "[Symbol.asyncIterator]", Builtin::kReturnReceiver, 0, kAdapt);
1099 native_context()->set_initial_async_iterator_prototype(
1100 *async_iterator_prototype);
1101
1102 // %AsyncFromSyncIteratorPrototype%
1103 // proposal-async-iteration/#sec-%asyncfromsynciteratorprototype%-object
1104 DirectHandle<JSObject> async_from_sync_iterator_prototype =
1105 factory()->NewJSObject(isolate()->object_function(),
1106 AllocationType::kOld);
1107 SimpleInstallFunction(isolate(), async_from_sync_iterator_prototype, "next",
1108 Builtin::kAsyncFromSyncIteratorPrototypeNext, 1,
1109 kDontAdapt);
1110 SimpleInstallFunction(isolate(), async_from_sync_iterator_prototype, "return",
1111 Builtin::kAsyncFromSyncIteratorPrototypeReturn, 1,
1112 kDontAdapt);
1113 SimpleInstallFunction(isolate(), async_from_sync_iterator_prototype, "throw",
1114 Builtin::kAsyncFromSyncIteratorPrototypeThrow, 1,
1115 kDontAdapt);
1116
1117 InstallToStringTag(isolate(), async_from_sync_iterator_prototype,
1118 "Async-from-Sync Iterator");
1119
1120 JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate(), async_from_sync_iterator_prototype,
1121 async_iterator_prototype);
1122
1123 DirectHandle<Map> async_from_sync_iterator_map =
1124 factory()->NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
1125 JS_ASYNC_FROM_SYNC_ITERATOR_TYPE,
1126 JSAsyncFromSyncIterator::kHeaderSize);
1127 Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), async_from_sync_iterator_map,
1128 async_from_sync_iterator_prototype);
1129 native_context()->set_async_from_sync_iterator_map(
1130 *async_from_sync_iterator_map);
1131
1132 // Async Generators
1133 DirectHandle<JSObject> async_generator_object_prototype =
1134 factory()->NewJSObject(isolate()->object_function(),
1135 AllocationType::kOld);
1136 DirectHandle<JSObject> async_generator_function_prototype =
1137 factory()->NewJSObject(isolate()->object_function(),
1138 AllocationType::kOld);
1139
1140 // %AsyncGenerator% / %AsyncGeneratorFunction%.prototype
1141 JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate(), async_generator_function_prototype,
1142 empty);
1143
1144 // The value of AsyncGeneratorFunction.prototype.prototype is the
1145 // %AsyncGeneratorPrototype% intrinsic object.
1146 // This property has the attributes
1147 // { [[Writable]]: false, [[Enumerable]]: false, [[Configurable]]: true }.
1148 JSObject::AddProperty(isolate(), async_generator_function_prototype,
1149 factory()->prototype_string(),
1150 async_generator_object_prototype,
1151 static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | READ_ONLY));
1152 JSObject::AddProperty(isolate(), async_generator_object_prototype,
1153 factory()->constructor_string(),
1154 async_generator_function_prototype,
1155 static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM | READ_ONLY));
1156 InstallToStringTag(isolate(), async_generator_function_prototype,
1157 "AsyncGeneratorFunction");
1158
1159 // %AsyncGeneratorPrototype%
1160 JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate(), async_generator_object_prototype,
1161 async_iterator_prototype);
1162 native_context()->set_initial_async_generator_prototype(
1163 *async_generator_object_prototype);
1164
1165 InstallToStringTag(isolate(), async_generator_object_prototype,
1166 "AsyncGenerator");
1167 SimpleInstallFunction(isolate(), async_generator_object_prototype, "next",
1168 Builtin::kAsyncGeneratorPrototypeNext, 1, kDontAdapt);
1169 SimpleInstallFunction(isolate(), async_generator_object_prototype, "return",
1170 Builtin::kAsyncGeneratorPrototypeReturn, 1, kDontAdapt);
1171 SimpleInstallFunction(isolate(), async_generator_object_prototype, "throw",
1172 Builtin::kAsyncGeneratorPrototypeThrow, 1, kDontAdapt);
1173
1174 // Create maps for generator functions and their prototypes. Store those
1175 // maps in the native context. The "prototype" property descriptor is
1176 // writable, non-enumerable, and non-configurable (as per ES6 draft
1177 // 04-14-15, section 25.2.4.3).
1178 // Async Generator functions do not have "caller" or "arguments" accessors.
1179 DirectHandle<Map> map;
1180 map = CreateNonConstructorMap(isolate(), isolate()->strict_function_map(),
1181 async_generator_function_prototype,
1182 "AsyncGeneratorFunction");
1183 native_context()->set_async_generator_function_map(*map);
1184
1185 map = CreateNonConstructorMap(
1186 isolate(), isolate()->strict_function_with_name_map(),
1187 async_generator_function_prototype, "AsyncGeneratorFunction with name");
1188 native_context()->set_async_generator_function_with_name_map(*map);
1189
1190 DirectHandle<JSFunction> object_function(native_context()->object_function(),
1191 isolate());
1192 DirectHandle<Map> async_generator_object_prototype_map =
1193 Map::Create(isolate(), 0);
1194 Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), async_generator_object_prototype_map,
1195 async_generator_object_prototype);
1196 native_context()->set_async_generator_object_prototype_map(
1197 *async_generator_object_prototype_map);
1198}
1199
1200void Genesis::CreateAsyncFunctionMaps(DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty) {
1201 // %AsyncFunctionPrototype% intrinsic
1202 DirectHandle<JSObject> async_function_prototype = factory()->NewJSObject(
1203 isolate()->object_function(), AllocationType::kOld);
1204 JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate(), async_function_prototype, empty);
1205
1206 InstallToStringTag(isolate(), async_function_prototype, "AsyncFunction");
1207
1208 DirectHandle<Map> map =
1209 Map::Copy(isolate(), isolate()->strict_function_without_prototype_map(),
1210 "AsyncFunction");
1211 Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), map, async_function_prototype);
1212 native_context()->set_async_function_map(*map);
1213
1214 map = Map::Copy(isolate(), isolate()->method_with_name_map(),
1215 "AsyncFunction with name");
1216 Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), map, async_function_prototype);
1217 native_context()->set_async_function_with_name_map(*map);
1218}
1219
1220void Genesis::CreateJSProxyMaps() {
1221 // Allocate maps for all Proxy types.
1222 // Next to the default proxy, we need maps indicating callable and
1223 // constructable proxies.
1224 DirectHandle<Map> proxy_map = factory()->NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
1225 JS_PROXY_TYPE, JSProxy::kSize, TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND);
1226 proxy_map->set_is_dictionary_map(true);
1227 proxy_map->set_may_have_interesting_properties(true);
1228 native_context()->set_proxy_map(*proxy_map);
1229 proxy_map->SetConstructor(native_context()->object_function());
1230
1231 DirectHandle<Map> proxy_callable_map =
1232 Map::Copy(isolate_, proxy_map, "callable Proxy");
1233 proxy_callable_map->set_is_callable(true);
1234 native_context()->set_proxy_callable_map(*proxy_callable_map);
1235 proxy_callable_map->SetConstructor(native_context()->function_function());
1236
1237 DirectHandle<Map> proxy_constructor_map =
1238 Map::Copy(isolate_, proxy_callable_map, "constructor Proxy");
1239 proxy_constructor_map->set_is_constructor(true);
1240 native_context()->set_proxy_constructor_map(*proxy_constructor_map);
1241
1242 {
1243 DirectHandle<Map> map = factory()->NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
1244 JS_OBJECT_TYPE, JSProxyRevocableResult::kSize,
1245 TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND, 2);
1246 Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate_, map, 2);
1247
1248 { // proxy
1249 Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), factory()->proxy_string(),
1250 JSProxyRevocableResult::kProxyIndex,
1251 NONE, Representation::Tagged());
1252 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
1253 }
1254 { // revoke
1255 Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(
1256 isolate(), factory()->revoke_string(),
1257 JSProxyRevocableResult::kRevokeIndex, NONE, Representation::Tagged());
1258 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
1259 }
1260
1261 Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), map, isolate()->initial_object_prototype());
1262 map->SetConstructor(native_context()->object_function());
1263
1264 native_context()->set_proxy_revocable_result_map(*map);
1265 }
1266}

1268namespace {
1269void ReplaceAccessors(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<Map> map,
1270 DirectHandle<String> name, PropertyAttributes attributes,
1271 DirectHandle<AccessorPair> accessor_pair) {
1272 Tagged<DescriptorArray> descriptors = map->instance_descriptors(isolate);
1273 InternalIndex entry = descriptors->SearchWithCache(isolate, *name, *map);
1274 Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(name, accessor_pair, attributes);
1275 descriptors->Replace(entry, &d);
1276}
1277
1278void InitializeJSArrayMaps(Isolate* isolate,
1279 DirectHandle<Context> native_context,
1280 DirectHandle<Map> initial_map) {
1281 // Replace all of the cached initial array maps in the native context with
1282 // the appropriate transitioned elements kind maps.
1283 DirectHandle<Map> current_map = initial_map;
1284 ElementsKind kind = current_map->elements_kind();
1285 DCHECK_EQ(GetInitialFastElementsKind(), kind);
1286 DCHECK_EQ(PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS, kind);
1287 DCHECK_EQ(Context::ArrayMapIndex(kind),
1288 Context::JS_ARRAY_PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS_MAP_INDEX);
1289 native_context->set(Context::ArrayMapIndex(kind), *current_map,
1290 UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER, kReleaseStore);
1291 for (int i = GetSequenceIndexFromFastElementsKind(kind) + 1;
1292 i < kFastElementsKindCount; ++i) {
1293 DirectHandle<Map> new_map;
1294 ElementsKind next_kind = GetFastElementsKindFromSequenceIndex(i);
1295 Tagged<Map> maybe_elements_transition = current_map->ElementsTransitionMap(
1296 isolate, ConcurrencyMode::kSynchronous);
1297 if (!maybe_elements_transition.is_null()) {
1298 new_map = direct_handle(maybe_elements_transition, isolate);
1299 } else {
1300 new_map = Map::CopyAsElementsKind(isolate, current_map, next_kind,
1301 INSERT_TRANSITION);
1302 }
1303 DCHECK_EQ(next_kind, new_map->elements_kind());
1304 native_context->set(Context::ArrayMapIndex(next_kind), *new_map,
1305 UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER, kReleaseStore);
1306 current_map = new_map;
1307 }
1308}
1309} // namespace
1310
1311void Genesis::AddRestrictedFunctionProperties(DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty) {
1312 PropertyAttributes rw_attribs = static_cast<PropertyAttributes>(DONT_ENUM);
1313 DirectHandle<JSFunction> thrower = GetThrowTypeErrorIntrinsic();
1314 DirectHandle<AccessorPair> accessors = factory()->NewAccessorPair();
1315 accessors->set_getter(*thrower);
1316 accessors->set_setter(*thrower);
1317
1318 DirectHandle<Map> map(empty->map(), isolate());
1319 ReplaceAccessors(isolate(), map, factory()->arguments_string(), rw_attribs,
1320 accessors);
1321 ReplaceAccessors(isolate(), map, factory()->caller_string(), rw_attribs,
1322 accessors);
1323}
1324
1325static void AddToWeakNativeContextList(Isolate* isolate,
1326 Tagged<Context> context) {
1327 DCHECK(IsNativeContext(context));
1328 Heap* heap = isolate->heap();
1329#ifdef DEBUG
1330 {
1331 DCHECK(IsUndefined(context->next_context_link(), isolate));
1332 // Check that context is not in the list yet.
1333 for (Tagged<Object> current = heap->native_contexts_list();
1334 !IsUndefined(current, isolate);
1335 current = Cast<Context>(current)->next_context_link()) {
1336 DCHECK(current != context);
1337 }
1338 }
1339#endif
1340 context->set(Context::NEXT_CONTEXT_LINK, heap->native_contexts_list(),
1341 UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER);
1342 heap->set_native_contexts_list(context);
1343}
1344
1345void Genesis::CreateRoots() {
1346 // Allocate the native context FixedArray first and then patch the
1347 // closure and extension object later (we need the empty function
1348 // and the global object, but in order to create those, we need the
1349 // native context).
1350 native_context_ = factory()->NewNativeContext();
1351
1352 AddToWeakNativeContextList(isolate(), *native_context());
1353 isolate()->set_context(*native_context());
1354}

1356void Genesis::InstallGlobalThisBinding() {
1357 DirectHandle<ScopeInfo> scope_info =
1358 isolate()->factory()->global_this_binding_scope_info();
1359 DirectHandle<Context> context =
1360 factory()->NewScriptContext(native_context(), scope_info);
1361
1362 // Go ahead and hook it up while we're at it.
1363 int slot = scope_info->ReceiverContextSlotIndex();
1364 DCHECK_EQ(slot, Context::MIN_CONTEXT_EXTENDED_SLOTS);
1365 context->set(slot, native_context()->global_proxy());
1366
1367 Handle<ScriptContextTable> script_contexts(
1368 native_context()->script_context_table(), isolate());
1369 DirectHandle<ScriptContextTable> new_script_contexts =
1370 ScriptContextTable::Add(isolate(), script_contexts, context, false);
1371 native_context()->set_script_context_table(*new_script_contexts);
1372}
1373
1374Handle<JSGlobalObject> Genesis::CreateNewGlobals(
1375 v8::Local<v8::ObjectTemplate> global_proxy_template,
1376 DirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> global_proxy) {
1377 // The argument global_proxy_template aka data is an ObjectTemplateInfo.
1378 // It has a constructor pointer that points at global_constructor which is a
1379 // FunctionTemplateInfo.
1380 // The global_proxy_constructor is used to (re)initialize the
1381 // global_proxy. The global_proxy_constructor also has a prototype_template
1382 // pointer that points at js_global_object_template which is an
1383 // ObjectTemplateInfo.
1384 // That in turn has a constructor pointer that points at
1385 // js_global_object_constructor which is a FunctionTemplateInfo.
1386 // js_global_object_constructor is used to make js_global_object_function
1387 // js_global_object_function is used to make the new global_object.
1388 //
1389 // --- G l o b a l ---
1390 // Step 1: Create a fresh JSGlobalObject.
1391 DirectHandle<JSFunction> js_global_object_function;
1392 DirectHandle<ObjectTemplateInfo> js_global_object_template;
1393 if (!global_proxy_template.IsEmpty()) {
1394 // Get prototype template of the global_proxy_template.
1395 DirectHandle<ObjectTemplateInfo> data =
1396 v8::Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*global_proxy_template);
1397 DirectHandle<FunctionTemplateInfo> global_constructor(
1398 Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(data->constructor()), isolate());
1399 DirectHandle<Object> proto_template(
1400 global_constructor->GetPrototypeTemplate(), isolate());
1401 if (!IsUndefined(*proto_template, isolate())) {
1402 js_global_object_template = Cast<ObjectTemplateInfo>(proto_template);
1403 }
1404 }
1405
1406 if (js_global_object_template.is_null()) {
1407 DirectHandle<String> name = factory()->empty_string();
1408 DirectHandle<JSObject> prototype =
1409 factory()->NewFunctionPrototype(isolate()->object_function());
1410 js_global_object_function = CreateFunctionForBuiltinWithPrototype(
1411 isolate(), name, Builtin::kIllegal, prototype, JS_GLOBAL_OBJECT_TYPE,
1412 JSGlobalObject::kHeaderSize, 0, MUTABLE, 0, kDontAdapt);
1413#ifdef DEBUG
1414 LookupIterator it(isolate(), prototype, factory()->constructor_string(),
1415 LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
1416 DirectHandle<Object> value = Object::GetProperty(&it).ToHandleChecked();
1417 DCHECK(it.IsFound());
1418 DCHECK_EQ(*isolate()->object_function(), *value);
1419#endif
1420 } else {
1421 DirectHandle<FunctionTemplateInfo> js_global_object_constructor(
1422 Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(js_global_object_template->constructor()),
1423 isolate());
1424 js_global_object_function = ApiNatives::CreateApiFunction(
1425 isolate(), isolate()->native_context(), js_global_object_constructor,
1426 factory()->the_hole_value(), JS_GLOBAL_OBJECT_TYPE);
1427 }
1428
1429 js_global_object_function->initial_map()->set_is_prototype_map(true);
1430 js_global_object_function->initial_map()->set_is_dictionary_map(true);
1431 js_global_object_function->initial_map()->set_may_have_interesting_properties(
1432 true);
1433 Handle<JSGlobalObject> global_object =
1434 factory()->NewJSGlobalObject(js_global_object_function);
1435
1436 // Step 2: (re)initialize the global proxy object.
1437 DirectHandle<JSFunction> global_proxy_function;
1438 if (global_proxy_template.IsEmpty()) {
1439 DirectHandle<String> name = factory()->empty_string();
1440 global_proxy_function = CreateFunctionForBuiltinWithPrototype(
1441 isolate(), name, Builtin::kIllegal, factory()->the_hole_value(),
1442 JS_GLOBAL_PROXY_TYPE, JSGlobalProxy::SizeWithEmbedderFields(0), 0,
1443 MUTABLE, 0, kDontAdapt);
1444 } else {
1445 DirectHandle<ObjectTemplateInfo> data =
1446 v8::Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*global_proxy_template);
1447 DirectHandle<FunctionTemplateInfo> global_constructor(
1448 Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(data->constructor()), isolate());
1449 global_proxy_function = ApiNatives::CreateApiFunction(
1450 isolate(), isolate()->native_context(), global_constructor,
1451 factory()->the_hole_value(), JS_GLOBAL_PROXY_TYPE);
1452 }
1453 global_proxy_function->initial_map()->set_is_access_check_needed(true);
1454 global_proxy_function->initial_map()->set_may_have_interesting_properties(
1455 true);
1456 native_context()->set_global_proxy_function(*global_proxy_function);
1457
1458 // Set the global object as the (hidden) __proto__ of the global proxy after
1459 // ConfigureGlobalObject
1460 factory()->ReinitializeJSGlobalProxy(global_proxy, global_proxy_function);
1461
1462 // Set up the pointer back from the global object to the global proxy.
1463 global_object->set_global_proxy(*global_proxy);
1464 // Set the native context of the global proxy.
1465 global_proxy->map()->set_map(isolate(), native_context()->meta_map());
1466 // Set the global proxy of the native context. If the native context has been
1467 // deserialized, the global proxy is already correctly set up by the
1468 // deserializer. Otherwise it's undefined.
1469 DCHECK(IsUndefined(native_context()->get(Context::GLOBAL_PROXY_INDEX),
1470 isolate()) ||
1471 native_context()->global_proxy_object() == *global_proxy);
1472 native_context()->set_global_proxy_object(*global_proxy);
1473
1474 return global_object;
1475}
1476
1477void Genesis::HookUpGlobalProxy(DirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> global_proxy) {
1478 // Re-initialize the global proxy with the global proxy function from the
1479 // snapshot, and then set up the link to the native context.
1480 DirectHandle<JSFunction> global_proxy_function(
1481 native_context()->global_proxy_function(), isolate());
1482 factory()->ReinitializeJSGlobalProxy(global_proxy, global_proxy_function);
1483 DirectHandle<JSObject> global_object(
1484 Cast<JSObject>(native_context()->global_object()), isolate());
1485 JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate(), global_proxy, global_object);
1486 global_proxy->map()->set_map(isolate(), native_context()->meta_map());
1487 DCHECK(native_context()->global_proxy() == *global_proxy);
1488}
1489
1490void Genesis::HookUpGlobalObject(DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> global_object) {
1491 DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> global_object_from_snapshot(
1492 Cast<JSGlobalObject>(native_context()->extension()), isolate());
1493 native_context()->set_extension(*global_object);
1494 native_context()->set_security_token(*global_object);
1495
1496 TransferNamedProperties(global_object_from_snapshot, global_object);
1497 if (global_object_from_snapshot->HasDictionaryElements()) {
1498 JSObject::NormalizeElements(global_object);
1499 }
1500 DCHECK_EQ(global_object_from_snapshot->GetElementsKind(),
1501 global_object->GetElementsKind());
1502 TransferIndexedProperties(global_object_from_snapshot, global_object);
1503}
1504
1505// See https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-ordinarycreatefromconstructor for details
1506// about intrinsicDefaultProto concept. In short it's about using proper
1507// prototype object from constructor's realm when the constructor has
1508// non-instance prototype.
1509static void InstallWithIntrinsicDefaultProto(Isolate* isolate,
1510 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function,
1511 int context_index) {
1512 DirectHandle<Smi> index(Smi::FromInt(context_index), isolate);
1513 JSObject::AddProperty(isolate, function,
1514 isolate->factory()->native_context_index_symbol(),
1515 index, NONE);
1516 isolate->native_context()->set(context_index, *function, UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER,
1517 kReleaseStore);
1518}
1519
1520void InstallError(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> global,
1521 DirectHandle<String> name, int context_index,
1522 Builtin error_constructor, int error_function_length) {
1523 Factory* factory = isolate->factory();
1524
1525 // Most Error objects consist of a message, a stack trace, and possibly a
1526 // cause. Reserve three in-object properties for these.
1527 const int in_object_properties = 3;
1528 const int kErrorObjectSize =
1529 JSObject::kHeaderSize + in_object_properties * kTaggedSize;
1530 DirectHandle<JSFunction> error_fun =
1531 InstallFunction(isolate, global, name, JS_ERROR_TYPE, kErrorObjectSize,
1532 in_object_properties, factory->the_hole_value(),
1533 error_constructor, error_function_length, kDontAdapt);
1534
1535 if (context_index == Context::ERROR_FUNCTION_INDEX) {
1536 SimpleInstallFunction(isolate, error_fun, "captureStackTrace",
1537 Builtin::kErrorCaptureStackTrace, 2, kDontAdapt);
1538 }
1539
1540 InstallWithIntrinsicDefaultProto(isolate, error_fun, context_index);
1541
1542 {
1543 // Setup %XXXErrorPrototype%.
1544 DirectHandle<JSObject> prototype(
1545 Cast<JSObject>(error_fun->instance_prototype()), isolate);
1546
1547 JSObject::AddProperty(isolate, prototype, factory->name_string(), name,
1548 DONT_ENUM);
1549 JSObject::AddProperty(isolate, prototype, factory->message_string(),
1550 factory->empty_string(), DONT_ENUM);
1551
1552 if (context_index == Context::ERROR_FUNCTION_INDEX) {
1553 DirectHandle<JSFunction> to_string_fun =
1554 SimpleInstallFunction(isolate, prototype, "toString",
1555 Builtin::kErrorPrototypeToString, 0, kAdapt);
1556 isolate->native_context()->set_error_to_string(*to_string_fun);
1557 isolate->native_context()->set_initial_error_prototype(*prototype);
1558 } else {
1559 DirectHandle<JSFunction> global_error = isolate->error_function();
1560 CHECK(JSReceiver::SetPrototype(isolate, error_fun, global_error, false,
1561 kThrowOnError)
1562 .FromMaybe(false));
1563 CHECK(JSReceiver::SetPrototype(
1564 isolate, prototype,
1565 direct_handle(global_error->prototype(), isolate), false,
1566 kThrowOnError)
1567 .FromMaybe(false));
1568 }
1569 }
1570
1571 DirectHandle<Map> initial_map(error_fun->initial_map(), isolate);
1572 Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate, initial_map, 3);
1573 const int kJSErrorErrorStackSymbolIndex = 0;
1574 const int kJSErrorErrorMessageSymbolIndex = 1;
1575
1576 { // error_stack_symbol
1577 Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(isolate, factory->error_stack_symbol(),
1578 kJSErrorErrorStackSymbolIndex,
1579 DONT_ENUM, Representation::Tagged());
1580 initial_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate, &d);
1581 }
1582 {
1583 // error_message_symbol
1584 Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(
1585 isolate, factory->error_message_symbol(),
1586 kJSErrorErrorMessageSymbolIndex, DONT_ENUM, Representation::Tagged());
1587 initial_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate, &d);
1588 }
1589 { // stack
1590 DirectHandle<AccessorPair> new_pair = factory->NewAccessorPair();
1591 new_pair->set_getter(*factory->error_stack_getter_fun_template());
1592 new_pair->set_setter(*factory->error_stack_setter_fun_template());
1593
1594 Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(factory->stack_string(),
1595 new_pair, DONT_ENUM);
1596 initial_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate, &d);
1597 }
1598}

1601
1602Handle<JSObject> InitializeTemporal(Isolate* isolate) {
1603 DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context = isolate->native_context();
1604
1605 // Already initialized?
1606 Handle<HeapObject> maybe_temporal(native_context->temporal_object(), isolate);
1607 if (IsJSObject(*maybe_temporal)) {
1608 return Cast<JSObject>(maybe_temporal);
1609 }
1610
1611 isolate->CountUsage(v8::Isolate::kTemporalObject);
1612
1613 // -- T e m p o r a l
1614 // #sec-temporal-objects
1615 Handle<JSObject> temporal = isolate->factory()->NewJSObject(
1616 isolate->object_function(), AllocationType::kOld);
1617
1618 // The initial value of the @@toStringTag property is the string value
1619 // *"Temporal"*.
1620 // https://github.com/tc39/proposal-temporal/issues/1539
1621 InstallToStringTag(isolate, temporal, "Temporal");
1622
1623 { // -- N o w
1624 // #sec-temporal-now-object
1625 DirectHandle<JSObject> now = isolate->factory()->NewJSObject(
1626 isolate->object_function(), AllocationType::kOld);
1627 JSObject::AddProperty(isolate, temporal, "Now", now, DONT_ENUM);
1628 InstallToStringTag(isolate, now, "Temporal.Now");
1629
1630 // Note: There are NO Temporal.Now.plainTime
1631 // See https://github.com/tc39/proposal-temporal/issues/1540
1632#define NOW_LIST(V) \
1633 V(timeZone, TimeZone, 0) \
1634 V(instant, Instant, 0) \
1635 V(plainDateTime, PlainDateTime, 1) \
1636 V(plainDateTimeISO, PlainDateTimeISO, 0) \
1637 V(zonedDateTime, ZonedDateTime, 1) \
1638 V(zonedDateTimeISO, ZonedDateTimeISO, 0) \
1639 V(plainDate, PlainDate, 1) \
1640 V(plainDateISO, PlainDateISO, 0) \
1641 V(plainTimeISO, PlainTimeISO, 0)
1642
1643#define INSTALL_NOW_FUNC(p, N, n) \
1644 SimpleInstallFunction(isolate, now, #p, Builtin::kTemporalNow##N, n, \
1645 kDontAdapt);
1646
1647 NOW_LIST(INSTALL_NOW_FUNC)
1648#undef INSTALL_NOW_FUNC
1649#undef NOW_LIST
1650 }
1651#define INSTALL_TEMPORAL_CTOR_AND_PROTOTYPE(N, U, NUM_ARGS) \
1652 DirectHandle<JSFunction> obj_func = InstallFunction( \
1653 isolate, temporal, #N, JS_TEMPORAL_##U##_TYPE, \
1654 JSTemporal##N::kHeaderSize, 0, isolate->factory()->the_hole_value(), \
1655 Builtin::kTemporal##N##Constructor, NUM_ARGS, kDontAdapt); \
1656 InstallWithIntrinsicDefaultProto(isolate, obj_func, \
1657 Context::JS_TEMPORAL_##U##_FUNCTION_INDEX); \
1658 DirectHandle<JSObject> prototype( \
1659 Cast<JSObject>(obj_func->instance_prototype()), isolate); \
1660 InstallToStringTag(isolate, prototype, "Temporal." #N);
1661
1662#define INSTALL_TEMPORAL_FUNC(T, name, N, arg) \
1663 SimpleInstallFunction(isolate, obj_func, #name, Builtin::kTemporal##T##N, \
1664 arg, kDontAdapt);
1665
1666 { // -- P l a i n D a t e
1667 // #sec-temporal-plaindate-objects
1668 // #sec-temporal.plaindate
1669 INSTALL_TEMPORAL_CTOR_AND_PROTOTYPE(PlainDate, PLAIN_DATE, 3)
1670 INSTALL_TEMPORAL_FUNC(PlainDate, from, From, 1)
1671 INSTALL_TEMPORAL_FUNC(PlainDate, compare, Compare, 2)
1672
1673#ifdef V8_INTL_SUPPORT
1674#define PLAIN_DATE_GETTER_LIST_INTL(V) \
1675 V(era, Era) \
1676 V(eraYear, EraYear)
1677#else
1678#define PLAIN_DATE_GETTER_LIST_INTL(V)
1679#endif // V8_INTL_SUPPORT
1680
1681#define PLAIN_DATE_GETTER_LIST(V) \
1682 PLAIN_DATE_GETTER_LIST_INTL(V) \
1683 V(calendar, Calendar) \
1684 V(year, Year) \
1685 V(month, Month) \
1686 V(monthCode, MonthCode) \
1687 V(day, Day) \
1688 V(dayOfWeek, DayOfWeek) \
1689 V(dayOfYear, DayOfYear) \
1690 V(weekOfYear, WeekOfYear) \
1691 V(daysInWeek, DaysInWeek) \
1692 V(daysInMonth, DaysInMonth) \
1693 V(daysInYear, DaysInYear) \
1694 V(monthsInYear, MonthsInYear) \
1695 V(inLeapYear, InLeapYear)
1696
1697#define INSTALL_PLAIN_DATE_GETTER_FUNC(p, N) \
1698 SimpleInstallGetter(isolate, prototype, isolate->factory()->p##_string(), \
1699 Builtin::kTemporalPlainDatePrototype##N, kAdapt);
1700
1701 PLAIN_DATE_GETTER_LIST(INSTALL_PLAIN_DATE_GETTER_FUNC)
1702#undef PLAIN_DATE_GETTER_LIST
1703#undef PLAIN_DATE_GETTER_LIST_INTL
1704#undef INSTALL_PLAIN_DATE_GETTER_FUNC
1705
1706#define PLAIN_DATE_FUNC_LIST(V) \
1707 V(toPlainYearMonth, ToPlainYearMonth, 0) \
1708 V(toPlainMonthDay, ToPlainMonthDay, 0) \
1709 V(getISOFiels, GetISOFields, 0) \
1710 V(add, Add, 1) \
1711 V(subtract, Subtract, 1) \
1712 V(with, With, 1) \
1713 V(withCalendar, WithCalendar, 1) \

1716 V(equals, Equals, 1) \
1717 V(getISOFields, GetISOFields, 0) \
1718 V(toLocaleString, ToLocaleString, 0) \
1719 V(toPlainDateTime, ToPlainDateTime, 0) \
1720 V(toZonedDateTime, ToZonedDateTime, 1) \
1721 V(toString, ToString, 0) \
1722 V(toJSON, ToJSON, 0) \
1723 V(valueOf, ValueOf, 0)
1724
1725#define INSTALL_PLAIN_DATE_FUNC(p, N, min) \
1726 SimpleInstallFunction(isolate, prototype, #p, \
1727 Builtin::kTemporalPlainDatePrototype##N, min, \
1728 kDontAdapt);
1729 PLAIN_DATE_FUNC_LIST(INSTALL_PLAIN_DATE_FUNC)
1730#undef PLAIN_DATE_FUNC_LIST
1731#undef INSTALL_PLAIN_DATE_FUNC
1732 }
1733 { // -- P l a i n T i m e
1734 // #sec-temporal-plaintime-objects
1735 // #sec-temporal.plaintime
1736 INSTALL_TEMPORAL_CTOR_AND_PROTOTYPE(PlainTime, PLAIN_TIME, 0)
1737 INSTALL_TEMPORAL_FUNC(PlainTime, from, From, 1)
1738 INSTALL_TEMPORAL_FUNC(PlainTime, compare, Compare, 2)
1739
1740#define PLAIN_TIME_GETTER_LIST(V) \

1742 V(hour, Hour) \

2245
2246void LazyInitializeDateToTemporalInstant(
2247 v8::Local<v8::Name> name, const v8::PropertyCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2248 Isolate* isolate = reinterpret_cast<Isolate*>(info.GetIsolate());
2249 InitializeTemporal(isolate);
2250 DirectHandle<JSFunction> function = SimpleCreateFunction(
2251 isolate, isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String("toTemporalInstant"),
2252 Builtin::kDatePrototypeToTemporalInstant, 0, kDontAdapt);
2253 info.GetReturnValue().Set(v8::Utils::ToLocal(function));
2254}
2255
2256void LazyInitializeGlobalThisTemporal(
2257 v8::Local<v8::Name> name, const v8::PropertyCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
2258 Isolate* isolate = reinterpret_cast<Isolate*>(info.GetIsolate());
2259 DirectHandle<JSObject> temporal = InitializeTemporal(isolate);
2260 info.GetReturnValue().Set(v8::Utils::ToLocal(temporal));
2261}

2265// This is only called if we are not using snapshots. The equivalent
2266// work in the snapshot case is done in HookUpGlobalObject.
2267void Genesis::InitializeGlobal(DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> global_object,
2268 DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty_function) {
2269 // --- N a t i v e C o n t e x t ---
2270 // Set extension and global object.
2271 native_context()->set_extension(*global_object);
2272 // Security setup: Set the security token of the native context to the global
2273 // object. This makes the security check between two different contexts fail
2274 // by default even in case of global object reinitialization.
2275 native_context()->set_security_token(*global_object);
2276
2277 Factory* factory = isolate_->factory();

2285 native_context()->set_function_context_map(*map);
2286
2287 map = factory->NewMapWithMetaMap(meta_map, CATCH_CONTEXT_TYPE,
2288 kVariableSizeSentinel);
2289 map->set_native_context(*native_context());
2290 native_context()->set_catch_context_map(*map);
2291
2292 map = factory->NewMapWithMetaMap(meta_map, WITH_CONTEXT_TYPE,
2293 kVariableSizeSentinel);
2294 map->set_native_context(*native_context());
2295 native_context()->set_with_context_map(*map);
2296
2297 map = factory->NewMapWithMetaMap(meta_map, DEBUG_EVALUATE_CONTEXT_TYPE,
2298 kVariableSizeSentinel);
2299 map->set_native_context(*native_context());
2300 native_context()->set_debug_evaluate_context_map(*map);
2301
2302 map = factory->NewMapWithMetaMap(meta_map, BLOCK_CONTEXT_TYPE,
2303 kVariableSizeSentinel);
2304 map->set_native_context(*native_context());
2305 native_context()->set_block_context_map(*map);
2306

2309 map->set_native_context(*native_context());
2310 native_context()->set_module_context_map(*map);
2311

2314 map->set_native_context(*native_context());
2315 native_context()->set_await_context_map(*map);

2318 kVariableSizeSentinel);

2320 native_context()->set_script_context_map(*map);
2321

4136 native_context()->set_intl_segment_iterator_map(*segment_iterator_map);
4137 }
4138 {
4139 // Set up the maps for SegmentDataObjects, with and without "isWordLike"
4140 // property.
4141 constexpr int kNumProperties = 3;
4142 constexpr int kNumPropertiesWithWordlike = kNumProperties + 1;
4143 constexpr int kInstanceSize =
4144 JSObject::kHeaderSize + kNumProperties * kTaggedSize;
4145 constexpr int kInstanceSizeWithWordlike =
4146 JSObject::kHeaderSize + kNumPropertiesWithWordlike * kTaggedSize;
4147 DirectHandle<Map> map = factory->NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
4148 JS_OBJECT_TYPE, kInstanceSize, TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND,
4149 kNumProperties);
4150 DirectHandle<Map> map_with_wordlike =
4151 factory->NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
4152 JS_OBJECT_TYPE, kInstanceSizeWithWordlike,
4153 TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND, kNumPropertiesWithWordlike);
4154 map->SetConstructor(native_context()->object_function());
4155 map_with_wordlike->SetConstructor(native_context()->object_function());
4156 map->set_prototype(*isolate_->initial_object_prototype());
4157 map_with_wordlike->set_prototype(*isolate_->initial_object_prototype());
4158 Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate_, map, kNumProperties);
4159 Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate_, map_with_wordlike,
4160 kNumPropertiesWithWordlike);
4161 int index = 0;
4162 { // segment
4163 Descriptor d =
4164 Descriptor::DataField(isolate_, factory->segment_string(),
4165 index++, NONE, Representation::Tagged());
4166 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate_, &d);
4167 map_with_wordlike->AppendDescriptor(isolate_, &d);
4168 }
4169 { // index
4170 Descriptor d =
4171 Descriptor::DataField(isolate_, factory->index_string(), index++,
4172 NONE, Representation::Tagged());
4173 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate_, &d);
4174 map_with_wordlike->AppendDescriptor(isolate_, &d);
4175 }
4176 { // input
4177 Descriptor d =
4178 Descriptor::DataField(isolate_, factory->input_string(), index++,
4179 NONE, Representation::Tagged());
4180 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate_, &d);
4181 map_with_wordlike->AppendDescriptor(isolate_, &d);
4182 }
4183 DCHECK_EQ(index, kNumProperties);
4184 { // isWordLike
4185 Descriptor d =
4186 Descriptor::DataField(isolate_, factory->isWordLike_string(),
4187 index++, NONE, Representation::Tagged());
4188 map_with_wordlike->AppendDescriptor(isolate_, &d);
4189 }
4190 DCHECK_EQ(index, kNumPropertiesWithWordlike);
4191 DCHECK(!map->is_dictionary_map());
4192 DCHECK(!map_with_wordlike->is_dictionary_map());
4193 native_context()->set_intl_segment_data_object_map(*map);
4194 native_context()->set_intl_segment_data_object_wordlike_map(
4195 *map_with_wordlike);
4196 }
4197 }
