6092// TODO(jgruber): Refactor this into some kind of meaningful organization. There
6093// is likely no reason remaining for these objects to be installed here. For
6094// example, global object setup done in this function could likely move to
6095// InitializeGlobal.
6096bool Genesis::InstallABunchOfRandomThings() {
6097 HandleScope scope(isolate());
6098
6099 auto fast_template_instantiations_cache =
6100 isolate()->factory()->NewFixedArrayWithHoles(
6101 TemplateInfo::kFastTemplateInstantiationsCacheSize);
6102 native_context()->set_fast_template_instantiations_cache(
6103 *fast_template_instantiations_cache);
6104
6105 auto slow_template_instantiations_cache = SimpleNumberDictionary::New(
6106 isolate(), ApiNatives::kInitialFunctionCacheSize);
6107 native_context()->set_slow_template_instantiations_cache(
6108 *slow_template_instantiations_cache);
6109
6110 auto wasm_debug_maps = isolate()->factory()->empty_fixed_array();
6111 native_context()->set_wasm_debug_maps(*wasm_debug_maps);
6112
6113 // Store the map for the %ObjectPrototype% after the natives has been compiled
6114 // and the Object function has been set up.
6115 {
6116 DirectHandle<JSFunction> object_function(
6117 native_context()->object_function(), isolate());
6118 DCHECK(Cast<JSObject>(object_function->initial_map()->prototype())
6119 ->HasFastProperties());
6120 native_context()->set_object_function_prototype(
6121 Cast<JSObject>(object_function->initial_map()->prototype()));
6122 native_context()->set_object_function_prototype_map(
6123 Cast<HeapObject>(object_function->initial_map()->prototype())->map());
6124 }
6125
6126 // Store the map for the %StringPrototype% after the natives has been compiled
6127 // and the String function has been set up.
6128 DirectHandle<JSFunction> string_function(native_context()->string_function(),
6129 isolate());
6130 Tagged<JSObject> string_function_prototype =
6131 Cast<JSObject>(string_function->initial_map()->prototype());
6132 DCHECK(string_function_prototype->HasFastProperties());
6133 native_context()->set_string_function_prototype_map(
6134 string_function_prototype->map());
6135
6136 DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> global_object(native_context()->global_object(),
6137 isolate());
6138
6139 // Install Global.decodeURI.
6140 InstallFunctionWithBuiltinId(isolate(), global_object, "decodeURI",
6141 Builtin::kGlobalDecodeURI, 1, kDontAdapt);
6142
6143 // Install Global.decodeURIComponent.
6144 InstallFunctionWithBuiltinId(isolate(), global_object, "decodeURIComponent",
6145 Builtin::kGlobalDecodeURIComponent, 1,
6146 kDontAdapt);
6147
6148 // Install Global.encodeURI.
6149 InstallFunctionWithBuiltinId(isolate(), global_object, "encodeURI",
6150 Builtin::kGlobalEncodeURI, 1, kDontAdapt);
6151
6152 // Install Global.encodeURIComponent.
6153 InstallFunctionWithBuiltinId(isolate(), global_object, "encodeURIComponent",
6154 Builtin::kGlobalEncodeURIComponent, 1,
6155 kDontAdapt);
6156
6157 // Install Global.escape.
6158 InstallFunctionWithBuiltinId(isolate(), global_object, "escape",
6159 Builtin::kGlobalEscape, 1, kDontAdapt);
6160
6161 // Install Global.unescape.
6162 InstallFunctionWithBuiltinId(isolate(), global_object, "unescape",
6163 Builtin::kGlobalUnescape, 1, kDontAdapt);
6164
6165 // Install Global.eval.
6166 {
6167 DirectHandle<JSFunction> eval = SimpleInstallFunction(
6168 isolate(), global_object, "eval", Builtin::kGlobalEval, 1, kDontAdapt);
6169 native_context()->set_global_eval_fun(*eval);
6170 }
6171
6172 // Install Global.isFinite
6173 InstallFunctionWithBuiltinId(isolate(), global_object, "isFinite",
6174 Builtin::kGlobalIsFinite, 1, kAdapt);
6175
6176 // Install Global.isNaN
6177 InstallFunctionWithBuiltinId(isolate(), global_object, "isNaN",
6178 Builtin::kGlobalIsNaN, 1, kAdapt);
6179
6180 // Install Array builtin functions.
6181 {
6182 DirectHandle<JSFunction> array_constructor(
6183 native_context()->array_function(), isolate());
6184 DirectHandle<JSArray> proto(Cast<JSArray>(array_constructor->prototype()),
6185 isolate());
6186
6187 // Verification of important array prototype properties.
6188 Tagged<Object> length = proto->length();
6189 CHECK(IsSmi(length));
6190 CHECK_EQ(Smi::ToInt(length), 0);
6191 CHECK(proto->HasSmiOrObjectElements());
6192 // This is necessary to enable fast checks for absence of elements
6193 // on Array.prototype and below.
6194 proto->set_elements(ReadOnlyRoots(heap()).empty_fixed_array());
6195 }
6196
6197 // Create a map for accessor property descriptors (a variant of JSObject
6198 // that predefines four properties get, set, configurable and enumerable).
6199 {
6200 // AccessorPropertyDescriptor initial map.
6201 DirectHandle<Map> map = factory()->NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
6202 JS_OBJECT_TYPE, JSAccessorPropertyDescriptor::kSize,
6203 TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND, 4);
6204 // Create the descriptor array for the property descriptor object.
6205 Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate(), map, 4);
6206
6207 { // get
6208 Descriptor d =
6209 Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), factory()->get_string(),
6210 JSAccessorPropertyDescriptor::kGetIndex, NONE,
6211 Representation::Tagged());
6212 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6213 }
6214 { // set
6215 Descriptor d =
6216 Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), factory()->set_string(),
6217 JSAccessorPropertyDescriptor::kSetIndex, NONE,
6218 Representation::Tagged());
6219 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6220 }
6221 { // enumerable
6222 Descriptor d =
6223 Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), factory()->enumerable_string(),
6224 JSAccessorPropertyDescriptor::kEnumerableIndex,
6225 NONE, Representation::Tagged());
6226 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6227 }
6228 { // configurable
6229 Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(
6230 isolate(), factory()->configurable_string(),
6231 JSAccessorPropertyDescriptor::kConfigurableIndex, NONE,
6232 Representation::Tagged());
6233 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6234 }
6235
6236 Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), map, isolate()->initial_object_prototype());
6237 map->SetConstructor(native_context()->object_function());
6238
6239 native_context()->set_accessor_property_descriptor_map(*map);
6240 }
6241
6242 // Create a map for data property descriptors (a variant of JSObject
6243 // that predefines four properties value, writable, configurable and
6244 // enumerable).
6245 {
6246 // DataPropertyDescriptor initial map.
6247 DirectHandle<Map> map = factory()->NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
6248 JS_OBJECT_TYPE, JSDataPropertyDescriptor::kSize,
6249 TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND, 4);
6250 // Create the descriptor array for the property descriptor object.
6251 Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate(), map, 4);
6252
6253 { // value
6254 Descriptor d =
6255 Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), factory()->value_string(),
6256 JSDataPropertyDescriptor::kValueIndex, NONE,
6257 Representation::Tagged());
6258 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6259 }
6260 { // writable
6261 Descriptor d =
6262 Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), factory()->writable_string(),
6263 JSDataPropertyDescriptor::kWritableIndex, NONE,
6264 Representation::Tagged());
6265 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6266 }
6267 { // enumerable
6268 Descriptor d =
6269 Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), factory()->enumerable_string(),
6270 JSDataPropertyDescriptor::kEnumerableIndex,
6271 NONE, Representation::Tagged());
6272 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6273 }
6274 { // configurable
6275 Descriptor d =
6276 Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), factory()->configurable_string(),
6277 JSDataPropertyDescriptor::kConfigurableIndex,
6278 NONE, Representation::Tagged());
6279 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6280 }
6281
6282 Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), map, isolate()->initial_object_prototype());
6283 map->SetConstructor(native_context()->object_function());
6284
6285 native_context()->set_data_property_descriptor_map(*map);
6286 }
6287
6288 {
6289 // -- TemplateLiteral JSArray Map
6290 DirectHandle<JSFunction> array_function(native_context()->array_function(),
6291 isolate());
6292 DirectHandle<Map> template_map(array_function->initial_map(), isolate_);
6293 template_map = Map::CopyAsElementsKind(isolate_, template_map,
6294 PACKED_ELEMENTS, OMIT_TRANSITION);
6295 DCHECK_GE(TemplateLiteralObject::kHeaderSize,
6296 template_map->instance_size());
6297 template_map->set_instance_size(TemplateLiteralObject::kHeaderSize);
6298 // Temporarily instantiate a full template_literal_object to get the final
6299 // map.
6300 auto template_object =
6301 Cast<JSArray>(factory()->NewJSObjectFromMap(template_map));
6302 {
6303 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6304 Tagged<JSArray> raw = *template_object;
6305 raw->set_elements(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate()).empty_fixed_array());
6306 raw->set_length(Smi::FromInt(0));
6307 }
6308
6309 // Install a "raw" data property for {raw_object} on {template_object}.
6310 // See ES#sec-gettemplateobject.
6311 PropertyDescriptor raw_desc;
6312 // Use arbrirary object {template_object} as ".raw" value.
6313 raw_desc.set_value(template_object);
6314 raw_desc.set_configurable(false);
6315 raw_desc.set_enumerable(false);
6316 raw_desc.set_writable(false);
6317 JSArray::DefineOwnProperty(isolate(), template_object,
6318 factory()->raw_string(), &raw_desc,
6319 Just(kThrowOnError))
6320 .ToChecked();
6321 // Install private symbol fields for function_literal_id and slot_id.
6322 raw_desc.set_value(direct_handle(Smi::zero(), isolate()));
6323 JSArray::DefineOwnProperty(
6324 isolate(), template_object,
6325 factory()->template_literal_function_literal_id_symbol(), &raw_desc,
6326 Just(kThrowOnError))
6327 .ToChecked();
6328 JSArray::DefineOwnProperty(isolate(), template_object,
6329 factory()->template_literal_slot_id_symbol(),
6330 &raw_desc, Just(kThrowOnError))
6331 .ToChecked();
6332
6333 // Freeze the {template_object} as well.
6334 JSObject::SetIntegrityLevel(isolate(), template_object, FROZEN,
6335 kThrowOnError)
6336 .ToChecked();
6337 {
6338 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6339 Tagged<DescriptorArray> desc =
6340 template_object->map()->instance_descriptors();
6341 {
6342 // Verify TemplateLiteralObject::kRawOffset
6343 InternalIndex descriptor_index = desc->Search(
6344 *factory()->raw_string(), desc->number_of_descriptors());
6345 FieldIndex index =
6346 FieldIndex::ForDescriptor(template_object->map(), descriptor_index);
6347 CHECK(index.is_inobject());
6348 CHECK_EQ(index.offset(), TemplateLiteralObject::kRawOffset);
6349 }
6350
6351 {
6352 // Verify TemplateLiteralObject::kFunctionLiteralIdOffset
6353 InternalIndex descriptor_index = desc->Search(
6354 *factory()->template_literal_function_literal_id_symbol(),
6355 desc->number_of_descriptors());
6356 FieldIndex index =
6357 FieldIndex::ForDescriptor(template_object->map(), descriptor_index);
6358 CHECK(index.is_inobject());
6359 CHECK_EQ(index.offset(),
6360 TemplateLiteralObject::kFunctionLiteralIdOffset);
6361 }
6362
6363 {
6364 // Verify TemplateLiteralObject::kSlotIdOffset
6365 InternalIndex descriptor_index =
6366 desc->Search(*factory()->template_literal_slot_id_symbol(),
6367 desc->number_of_descriptors());
6368 FieldIndex index =
6369 FieldIndex::ForDescriptor(template_object->map(), descriptor_index);
6370 CHECK(index.is_inobject());
6371 CHECK_EQ(index.offset(), TemplateLiteralObject::kSlotIdOffset);
6372 }
6373 }
6374
6375 native_context()->set_js_array_template_literal_object_map(
6376 template_object->map());
6377 }
6378
6379 // Create a constructor for RegExp results (a variant of Array that
6380 // predefines the properties index, input, and groups).
6381 {
6382 // JSRegExpResult initial map.
6383 // Add additional slack to the initial map in case regexp_match_indices
6384 // are enabled to account for the additional descriptor.
6385 DirectHandle<Map> initial_map = CreateInitialMapForArraySubclass(
6386 JSRegExpResult::kSize, JSRegExpResult::kInObjectPropertyCount);
6387
6388 // index descriptor.
6389 {
6390 Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), factory()->index_string(),
6391 JSRegExpResult::kIndexIndex, NONE,
6392 Representation::Tagged());
6393 initial_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6394 }
6395
6396 // input descriptor.
6397 {
6398 Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), factory()->input_string(),
6399 JSRegExpResult::kInputIndex, NONE,
6400 Representation::Tagged());
6401 initial_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6402 }
6403
6404 // groups descriptor.
6405 {
6406 Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(
6407 isolate(), factory()->groups_string(), JSRegExpResult::kGroupsIndex,
6408 NONE, Representation::Tagged());
6409 initial_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6410 }
6411
6412 // Private internal only fields. All of the remaining fields have special
6413 // symbols to prevent their use in Javascript.
6414 {
6415 PropertyAttributes attribs = DONT_ENUM;
6416
6417 // names descriptor.
6418 {
6419 Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(
6420 isolate(), factory()->regexp_result_names_symbol(),
6421 JSRegExpResult::kNamesIndex, attribs, Representation::Tagged());
6422 initial_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6423 }
6424
6425 // regexp_input_index descriptor.
6426 {
6427 Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(
6428 isolate(), factory()->regexp_result_regexp_input_symbol(),
6429 JSRegExpResult::kRegExpInputIndex, attribs,
6430 Representation::Tagged());
6431 initial_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6432 }
6433
6434 // regexp_last_index descriptor.
6435 {
6436 Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(
6437 isolate(), factory()->regexp_result_regexp_last_index_symbol(),
6438 JSRegExpResult::kRegExpLastIndex, attribs,
6439 Representation::Tagged());
6440 initial_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6441 }
6442 }
6443
6444 // Set up the map for RegExp results objects for regexps with the /d flag.
6445 DirectHandle<Map> initial_with_indices_map =
6446 Map::Copy(isolate(), initial_map, "JSRegExpResult with indices");
6447 initial_with_indices_map->set_instance_size(
6448 JSRegExpResultWithIndices::kSize);
6449 DCHECK_EQ(initial_with_indices_map->GetInObjectProperties(),
6450 JSRegExpResultWithIndices::kInObjectPropertyCount);
6451
6452 // indices descriptor
6453 {
6454 Descriptor d =
6455 Descriptor::DataField(isolate(), factory()->indices_string(),
6456 JSRegExpResultWithIndices::kIndicesIndex, NONE,
6457 Representation::Tagged());
6458 Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate(), initial_with_indices_map, 1);
6459 initial_with_indices_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6460 }
6461
6462 native_context()->set_regexp_result_map(*initial_map);
6463 native_context()->set_regexp_result_with_indices_map(
6464 *initial_with_indices_map);
6465 }
6466
6467 // Create a constructor for JSRegExpResultIndices (a variant of Array that
6468 // predefines the groups property).
6469 {
6470 // JSRegExpResultIndices initial map.
6471 DirectHandle<Map> initial_map = CreateInitialMapForArraySubclass(
6472 JSRegExpResultIndices::kSize,
6473 JSRegExpResultIndices::kInObjectPropertyCount);
6474
6475 // groups descriptor.
6476 {
6477 Descriptor d = Descriptor::DataField(
6478 isolate(), factory()->groups_string(),
6479 JSRegExpResultIndices::kGroupsIndex, NONE, Representation::Tagged());
6480 initial_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6481 DCHECK_EQ(initial_map->LastAdded().as_int(),
6482 JSRegExpResultIndices::kGroupsDescriptorIndex);
6483 }
6484
6485 native_context()->set_regexp_result_indices_map(*initial_map);
6486 }
6487
6488 // Add @@iterator method to the arguments object maps.
6489 {
6490 PropertyAttributes attribs = DONT_ENUM;
6491 DirectHandle<AccessorInfo> arguments_iterator =
6492 factory()->arguments_iterator_accessor();
6493 {
6494 Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(factory()->iterator_symbol(),
6495 arguments_iterator, attribs);
6496 DirectHandle<Map> map(native_context()->sloppy_arguments_map(),
6497 isolate());
6498 Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate(), map, 1);
6499 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6500 }
6501 {
6502 Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(factory()->iterator_symbol(),
6503 arguments_iterator, attribs);
6504 DirectHandle<Map> map(native_context()->fast_aliased_arguments_map(),
6505 isolate());
6506 Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate(), map, 1);
6507 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6508 }
6509 {
6510 Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(factory()->iterator_symbol(),
6511 arguments_iterator, attribs);
6512 DirectHandle<Map> map(native_context()->slow_aliased_arguments_map(),
6513 isolate());
6514 Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate(), map, 1);
6515 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6516 }
6517 {
6518 Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(factory()->iterator_symbol(),
6519 arguments_iterator, attribs);
6520 DirectHandle<Map> map(native_context()->strict_arguments_map(),
6521 isolate());
6522 Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate(), map, 1);
6523 map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
6524 }
6525 }
6526 {
6527 DirectHandle<OrderedHashSet> promises =
6528 OrderedHashSet::Allocate(isolate(), 0).ToHandleChecked();
6529 native_context()->set_atomics_waitasync_promises(*promises);
6530 }
6531
6532 return true;
6533}
6534
6535bool Genesis::InstallExtrasBindings() {
6536 HandleScope scope(isolate());
6537
6538 DirectHandle<JSObject> extras_binding = factory()->NewJSObjectWithNullProto();
6539
6540 // binding.isTraceCategoryEnabled(category)
6541 SimpleInstallFunction(isolate(), extras_binding, "isTraceCategoryEnabled",
6542 Builtin::kIsTraceCategoryEnabled, 1, kAdapt);
6543
6544 // binding.trace(phase, category, name, id, data)
6545 SimpleInstallFunction(isolate(), extras_binding, "trace", Builtin::kTrace, 5,
6546 kAdapt);
6547
6548#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA
6549 // binding.getContinuationPreservedEmbedderData()
6550 SimpleInstallFunction(
6551 isolate(), extras_binding, "getContinuationPreservedEmbedderData",
6552 Builtin::kGetContinuationPreservedEmbedderData, 0, kAdapt);
6553
6554 // binding.setContinuationPreservedEmbedderData(value)
6555 SimpleInstallFunction(
6556 isolate(), extras_binding, "setContinuationPreservedEmbedderData",
6557 Builtin::kSetContinuationPreservedEmbedderData, 1, kAdapt);
6558#endif // V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA
6559
6560 InitializeConsole(extras_binding);
6561
6562 native_context()->set_extras_binding_object(*extras_binding);
6563
6564 return true;
6565}
6566
6567void Genesis::InitializeMapCaches() {
6568 {
6569 DirectHandle<NormalizedMapCache> cache = NormalizedMapCache::New(isolate());
6570 native_context()->set_normalized_map_cache(*cache);
6571 }
6572
6573 {
6574 DirectHandle<WeakFixedArray> cache = factory()->NewWeakFixedArray(
6575 JSObject::kMapCacheSize, AllocationType::kOld);
6576
6577 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6578 for (int i = 0; i < JSObject::kMapCacheSize; i++) {
6579 cache->set(i, ClearedValue(isolate()));
6580 }
6581 native_context()->set_map_cache(*cache);
6582 Tagged<Map> initial = native_context()->object_function()->initial_map();
6583 cache->set(0, MakeWeak(initial));
6584 cache->set(initial->GetInObjectProperties(), MakeWeak(initial));
6585 }
6586}
6587
6588bool Bootstrapper::InstallExtensions(DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context,
6589 v8::ExtensionConfiguration* extensions) {
6590 // Don't install extensions into the snapshot.
6591 if (isolate_->serializer_enabled()) return true;
6592 BootstrapperActive active(this);
6593 v8::Context::Scope context_scope(Utils::ToLocal(native_context));
6594 return Genesis::InstallExtensions(isolate_, native_context, extensions) &&
6595 Genesis::InstallSpecialObjects(isolate_, native_context);
6596}
6597
6598bool Genesis::InstallSpecialObjects(
6599 Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context) {
6600 HandleScope scope(isolate);
6601
6602 // Error.stackTraceLimit.
6603 {
6604 DirectHandle<JSObject> Error = isolate->error_function();
6605 DirectHandle<String> name = isolate->factory()->stackTraceLimit_string();
6606 DirectHandle<Smi> stack_trace_limit(
6607 Smi::FromInt(v8_flags.stack_trace_limit), isolate);
6608 JSObject::AddProperty(isolate, Error, name, stack_trace_limit, NONE);
6609 }
6610
6611#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
6612 WasmJs::Install(isolate);
6613#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
6614
6615#ifdef V8_ENABLE_MEMORY_CORRUPTION_API
6616 if (v8_flags.expose_memory_corruption_api) {
6617 SandboxTesting::InstallMemoryCorruptionApi(isolate);
6618 }
6619#endif // V8_ENABLE_MEMORY_CORRUPTION_API
6620
6621 return true;
6622}
6623
6624static uint32_t Hash(RegisteredExtension* extension) {
6625 return v8::internal::ComputePointerHash(extension);
6626}
6627
6628Genesis::ExtensionStates::ExtensionStates() : map_(8) {}
6629
6630Genesis::ExtensionTraversalState Genesis::ExtensionStates::get_state(
6631 RegisteredExtension* extension) {
6632 base::HashMap::Entry* entry = map_.Lookup(extension, Hash(extension));
6633 if (entry == nullptr) {
6634 return UNVISITED;
6635 }
6636 return static_cast<ExtensionTraversalState>(
6637 reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(entry->value));
6638}
6639
6640void Genesis::ExtensionStates::set_state(RegisteredExtension* extension,
6641 ExtensionTraversalState state) {
6642 map_.LookupOrInsert(extension, Hash(extension))->value =
6643 reinterpret_cast<void*>(static_cast<intptr_t>(state));
6644}
6645
6646bool Genesis::InstallExtensions(Isolate* isolate,
6647 DirectHandle<Context> native_context,
6648 v8::ExtensionConfiguration* extensions) {
6649 ExtensionStates extension_states; // All extensions have state UNVISITED.
6650 return InstallAutoExtensions(isolate, &extension_states) &&
6651 (!v8_flags.expose_gc ||
6652 InstallExtension(isolate, "v8/gc", &extension_states)) &&
6653 (!v8_flags.expose_externalize_string ||
6654 InstallExtension(isolate, "v8/externalize", &extension_states)) &&
6655 (!(v8_flags.expose_statistics ||
6656 TracingFlags::is_gc_stats_enabled()) ||
6657 InstallExtension(isolate, "v8/statistics", &extension_states)) &&
6658 (!v8_flags.expose_trigger_failure ||
6659 InstallExtension(isolate, "v8/trigger-failure", &extension_states)) &&
6660 (!v8_flags.expose_ignition_statistics ||
6661 InstallExtension(isolate, "v8/ignition-statistics",
6662 &extension_states)) &&
6663 (!isValidCpuTraceMarkFunctionName() ||
6664 InstallExtension(isolate, "v8/cpumark", &extension_states)) &&
6665#ifdef V8_FUZZILLI
6666 InstallExtension(isolate, "v8/fuzzilli", &extension_states) &&
6667#endif
6668#ifdef ENABLE_VTUNE_TRACEMARK
6669 (!v8_flags.enable_vtune_domain_support ||
6670 InstallExtension(isolate, "v8/vtunedomain", &extension_states)) &&
6671#endif // ENABLE_VTUNE_TRACEMARK
6672 InstallRequestedExtensions(isolate, extensions, &extension_states);
6673}
6674
6675bool Genesis::InstallAutoExtensions(Isolate* isolate,
6676 ExtensionStates* extension_states) {
6677 for (v8::RegisteredExtension* it = v8::RegisteredExtension::first_extension();
6678 it != nullptr; it = it->next()) {
6679 if (it->extension()->auto_enable() &&
6680 !InstallExtension(isolate, it, extension_states)) {
6681 return false;
6682 }
6683 }
6684 return true;
6685}
6686
6687bool Genesis::InstallRequestedExtensions(Isolate* isolate,
6688 v8::ExtensionConfiguration* extensions,
6689 ExtensionStates* extension_states) {
6690 for (const char** it = extensions->begin(); it != extensions->end(); ++it) {
6691 if (!InstallExtension(isolate, *it, extension_states)) return false;
6692 }
6693 return true;
6694}
6695
6696// Installs a named extension. This methods is unoptimized and does
6697// not scale well if we want to support a large number of extensions.
6698bool Genesis::InstallExtension(Isolate* isolate, const char* name,
6699 ExtensionStates* extension_states) {
6700 for (v8::RegisteredExtension* it = v8::RegisteredExtension::first_extension();
6701 it != nullptr; it = it->next()) {
6702 if (strcmp(name, it->extension()->name()) == 0) {
6703 return InstallExtension(isolate, it, extension_states);
6704 }
6705 }
6706 return Utils::ApiCheck(false, "v8::Context::New()",
6707 "Cannot find required extension");
6708}
6709
6710bool Genesis::InstallExtension(Isolate* isolate,
6711 v8::RegisteredExtension* current,
6712 ExtensionStates* extension_states) {
6713 HandleScope scope(isolate);
6714
6715 if (extension_states->get_state(current) == INSTALLED) return true;
6716 // The current node has already been visited so there must be a
6717 // cycle in the dependency graph; fail.
6718 if (!Utils::ApiCheck(extension_states->get_state(current) != VISITED,
6719 "v8::Context::New()", "Circular extension dependency")) {
6720 return false;
6721 }
6722 DCHECK(extension_states->get_state(current) == UNVISITED);
6723 extension_states->set_state(current, VISITED);
6724 v8::Extension* extension = current->extension();
6725 // Install the extension's dependencies
6726 for (int i = 0; i < extension->dependency_count(); i++) {
6727 if (!InstallExtension(isolate, extension->dependencies()[i],
6728 extension_states)) {
6729 return false;
6730 }
6731 }
6732 if (!CompileExtension(isolate, extension)) {
6733 // We print out the name of the extension that fail to install.
6734 // When an error is thrown during bootstrapping we automatically print
6735 // the line number at which this happened to the console in the isolate
6736 // error throwing functionality.
6737 base::OS::PrintError("Error installing extension '%s'.\n",
6738 current->extension()->name());
6739 return false;
6740 }
6741
6742 DCHECK(!isolate->has_exception());
6743 extension_states->set_state(current, INSTALLED);
6744 return true;
6745}
6746
6747bool Genesis::ConfigureGlobalObject(
6748 v8::Local<v8::ObjectTemplate> global_proxy_template) {
6749 DirectHandle<JSObject> global_proxy(native_context()->global_proxy(),
6750 isolate());
6751 DirectHandle<JSObject> global_object(native_context()->global_object(),
6752 isolate());
6753
6754 if (!global_proxy_template.IsEmpty()) {
6755 // Configure the global proxy object.
6756 DirectHandle<ObjectTemplateInfo> global_proxy_data =
6757 v8::Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*global_proxy_template);
6758 if (!ConfigureApiObject(global_proxy, global_proxy_data)) {
6759 base::OS::PrintError("V8 Error: Failed to configure global_proxy_data\n");
6760 return false;
6761 }
6762
6763 // Configure the global object.
6764 DirectHandle<FunctionTemplateInfo> proxy_constructor(
6765 Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(global_proxy_data->constructor()),
6766 isolate());
6767 if (!IsUndefined(proxy_constructor->GetPrototypeTemplate(), isolate())) {
6768 DirectHandle<ObjectTemplateInfo> global_object_data(
6769 Cast<ObjectTemplateInfo>(proxy_constructor->GetPrototypeTemplate()),
6770 isolate());
6771 if (!ConfigureApiObject(global_object, global_object_data)) {
6772 base::OS::PrintError(
6773 "V8 Error: Failed to configure global_object_data\n");
6774 return false;
6775 }
6776 }
6777 }
6778
6779 JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate(), global_proxy, global_object);
6780
6781 native_context()->set_array_buffer_map(
6782 native_context()->array_buffer_fun()->initial_map());
6783
6784 return true;
6785}
6786
6787bool Genesis::ConfigureApiObject(
6788 DirectHandle<JSObject> object,
6789 DirectHandle<ObjectTemplateInfo> object_template) {
6790 DCHECK(!object_template.is_null());
6791 DCHECK(Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(object_template->constructor())
6792 ->IsTemplateFor(object->map()));
6793
6794 MaybeDirectHandle<JSObject> maybe_obj =
6795 ApiNatives::InstantiateObject(object->GetIsolate(), object_template);
6796 DirectHandle<JSObject> instantiated_template;
6797 if (!maybe_obj.ToHandle(&instantiated_template)) {
6798 DCHECK(isolate()->has_exception());
6799
6800 DirectHandle<String> message =
6801 ErrorUtils::ToString(isolate_,
6802 direct_handle(isolate_->exception(), isolate_))
6803 .ToHandleChecked();
6804 base::OS::PrintError(
6805 "V8 Error: Exception in Genesis::ConfigureApiObject: %s\n",
6806 message->ToCString().get());
6807
6808 isolate()->clear_exception();
6809 return false;
6810 }
6811 TransferObject(instantiated_template, object);
6812 return true;
6813}
6814
6815static bool PropertyAlreadyExists(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSObject> to,
6816 DirectHandle<Name> key) {
6817 LookupIterator it(isolate, to, key, LookupIterator::OWN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
6818 CHECK_NE(LookupIterator::ACCESS_CHECK, it.state());
6819 return it.IsFound();
6820}
6821
6822void Genesis::TransferNamedProperties(DirectHandle<JSObject> from,
6823 DirectHandle<JSObject> to) {
6824 // If JSObject::AddProperty asserts due to already existing property,
6825 // it is likely due to both global objects sharing property name(s).
6826 // Merging those two global objects is impossible.
6827 // The global template must not create properties that already exist
6828 // in the snapshotted global object.
6829 if (from->HasFastProperties()) {
6830 DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> descs(
6831 from->map()->instance_descriptors(isolate()), isolate());
6832 for (InternalIndex i : from->map()->IterateOwnDescriptors()) {
6833 PropertyDetails details = descs->GetDetails(i);
6834 if (details.location() == PropertyLocation::kField) {
6835 if (details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData) {
6836 HandleScope inner(isolate());
6837 DirectHandle<Name> key(descs->GetKey(i), isolate());
6838 // If the property is already there we skip it.
6839 if (PropertyAlreadyExists(isolate(), to, key)) continue;
6840 FieldIndex index = FieldIndex::ForDetails(from->map(), details);
6841 DirectHandle<Object> value = JSObject::FastPropertyAt(
6842 isolate(), from, details.representation(), index);
6843 JSObject::AddProperty(isolate(), to, key, value,
6844 details.attributes());
6845 } else {
6846 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kAccessor, details.kind());
6847 UNREACHABLE();
6848 }
6849
6850 } else {
6851 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyLocation::kDescriptor, details.location());
6852 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kAccessor, details.kind());
6853 DirectHandle<Name> key(descs->GetKey(i), isolate());
6854 // If the property is already there we skip it.
6855 if (PropertyAlreadyExists(isolate(), to, key)) continue;
6856 HandleScope inner(isolate());
6857 DCHECK(!to->HasFastProperties());
6858 // Add to dictionary.
6859 DirectHandle<Object> value(descs->GetStrongValue(i), isolate());
6860 PropertyDetails d(PropertyKind::kAccessor, details.attributes(),
6861 PropertyCellType::kMutable);
6862 JSObject::SetNormalizedProperty(to, key, value, d);
6863 }
6864 }
6865 } else if (IsJSGlobalObject(*from)) {
6866 // Copy all keys and values in enumeration order.
6867 DirectHandle<GlobalDictionary> properties(
6868 Cast<JSGlobalObject>(*from)->global_dictionary(kAcquireLoad),
6869 isolate());
6870 DirectHandle<FixedArray> indices =
6871 GlobalDictionary::IterationIndices(isolate(), properties);
6872 for (int i = 0; i < indices->length(); i++) {
6873 InternalIndex index(Smi::ToInt(indices->get(i)));
6874 DirectHandle<PropertyCell> cell(properties->CellAt(index), isolate());
6875 DirectHandle<Name> key(cell->name(), isolate());
6876 // If the property is already there we skip it.
6877 if (PropertyAlreadyExists(isolate(), to, key)) continue;
6878 // Set the property.
6879 DirectHandle<Object> value(cell->value(), isolate());
6880 if (IsTheHole(*value, isolate())) continue;
6881 PropertyDetails details = cell->property_details();
6882 if (details.kind() == PropertyKind::kData) {
6883 JSObject::AddProperty(isolate(), to, key, value, details.attributes());
6884 } else {
6885 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kAccessor, details.kind());
6886 DCHECK(!to->HasFastProperties());
6887 PropertyDetails d(PropertyKind::kAccessor, details.attributes(),
6888 PropertyCellType::kMutable);
6889 JSObject::SetNormalizedProperty(to, key, value, d);
6890 }
6891 }
6892
6893 } else if (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
6894 // Copy all keys and values in enumeration order.
6895 DirectHandle<SwissNameDictionary> properties(
6896 from->property_dictionary_swiss(), isolate());
6897 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate());
6898 for (InternalIndex entry : properties->IterateEntriesOrdered()) {
6899 Tagged<Object> raw_key;
6900 if (!properties->ToKey(roots, entry, &raw_key)) continue;
6901
6902 DCHECK(IsName(raw_key));
6903 DirectHandle<Name> key(Cast<Name>(raw_key), isolate());
6904 // If the property is already there we skip it.
6905 if (PropertyAlreadyExists(isolate(), to, key)) continue;
6906 // Set the property.
6907 DirectHandle<Object> value(properties->ValueAt(entry), isolate());
6908 DCHECK(!IsCell(*value));
6909 DCHECK(!IsTheHole(*value, isolate()));
6910 PropertyDetails details = properties->DetailsAt(entry);
6911 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, details.kind());
6912 JSObject::AddProperty(isolate(), to, key, value, details.attributes());
6913 }
6914 } else {
6915 // Copy all keys and values in enumeration order.
6916 DirectHandle<NameDictionary> properties(from->property_dictionary(),
6917 isolate());
6918 DirectHandle<FixedArray> key_indices =
6919 NameDictionary::IterationIndices(isolate(), properties);
6920 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate());
6921 for (int i = 0; i < key_indices->length(); i++) {
6922 InternalIndex key_index(Smi::ToInt(key_indices->get(i)));
6923 Tagged<Object> raw_key = properties->KeyAt(key_index);
6924 DCHECK(properties->IsKey(roots, raw_key));
6925 DCHECK(IsName(raw_key));
6926 DirectHandle<Name> key(Cast<Name>(raw_key), isolate());
6927 // If the property is already there we skip it.
6928 if (PropertyAlreadyExists(isolate(), to, key)) continue;
6929 // Set the property.
6930 DirectHandle<Object> value(properties->ValueAt(key_index), isolate());
6931 DCHECK(!IsCell(*value));
6932 DCHECK(!IsTheHole(*value, isolate()));
6933 PropertyDetails details = properties->DetailsAt(key_index);
6934 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, details.kind());
6935 JSObject::AddProperty(isolate(), to, key, value, details.attributes());
6936 }
6937 }
6938}
6939
6940void Genesis::TransferIndexedProperties(DirectHandle<JSObject> from,
6941 DirectHandle<JSObject> to) {
6942 // Cloning the elements array is sufficient.
6943 Handle<FixedArray> from_elements(Cast<FixedArray>(from->elements()),
6944 isolate());
6945 DirectHandle<FixedArray> to_elements =
6946 factory()->CopyFixedArray(from_elements);
6947 to->set_elements(*to_elements);
6948}
6949
6950void Genesis::TransferObject(DirectHandle<JSObject> from,
6951 DirectHandle<JSObject> to) {
6952 HandleScope outer(isolate());
6953
6954 DCHECK(!IsJSArray(*from));
6955 DCHECK(!IsJSArray(*to));
6956
6957 TransferNamedProperties(from, to);
6958 TransferIndexedProperties(from, to);
6959
6960 // Transfer the prototype (new map is needed).
6961 DirectHandle<JSPrototype> proto(from->map()->prototype(), isolate());
6962 JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate(), to, proto);
6963}
6964
6965Handle<Map> Genesis::CreateInitialMapForArraySubclass(int size,
6966 int inobject_properties) {
6967 // Find global.Array.prototype to inherit from.
6968 DirectHandle<JSFunction> array_constructor(native_context()->array_function(),
6969 isolate());
6970 DirectHandle<JSObject> array_prototype(
6971 native_context()->initial_array_prototype(), isolate());
6972
6973 // Add initial map.
6974 Handle<Map> initial_map = factory()->NewContextfulMapForCurrentContext(
6975 JS_ARRAY_TYPE, size, TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND, inobject_properties);
6976 initial_map->SetConstructor(*array_constructor);
6977
6978 // Set prototype on map.
6979 initial_map->set_has_non_instance_prototype(false);
6980 Map::SetPrototype(isolate(), initial_map, array_prototype);
6981
6982 // Update map with length accessor from Array.
6983 static constexpr int kTheLengthAccessor = 1;
6984 Map::EnsureDescriptorSlack(isolate(), initial_map,
6985 inobject_properties + kTheLengthAccessor);
6986
6987 // length descriptor.
6988 {
6989 Tagged<JSFunction> array_function = native_context()->array_function();
6990 DirectHandle<DescriptorArray> array_descriptors(
6991 array_function->initial_map()->instance_descriptors(isolate()),
6992 isolate());
6993 DirectHandle<String> length = factory()->length_string();
6994 InternalIndex old = array_descriptors->SearchWithCache(
6995 isolate(), *length, array_function->initial_map());
6996 DCHECK(old.is_found());
6997 Descriptor d = Descriptor::AccessorConstant(
6998 length,
6999 direct_handle(array_descriptors->GetStrongValue(old), isolate()),
7000 array_descriptors->GetDetails(old).attributes());
7001 initial_map->AppendDescriptor(isolate(), &d);
7002 }
7003 return initial_map;
7004}
7005
7006Genesis::Genesis(Isolate* isolate,
7007 MaybeDirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> maybe_global_proxy,
7008 v8::Local<v8::ObjectTemplate> global_proxy_template,
7009 size_t context_snapshot_index,
7010 DeserializeEmbedderFieldsCallback embedder_fields_deserializer,
7011 v8::MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue)
7012 : isolate_(isolate), active_(isolate->bootstrapper()) {
7013 RCS_SCOPE(isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kGenesis);
7014 result_ = {};
7015 global_proxy_ = {};
7016
7017 // Before creating the roots we must save the context and restore it
7018 // on all function exits.
7019 SaveContext saved_context(isolate);
7020
7021 // The deserializer needs to hook up references to the global proxy.
7022 // Create an uninitialized global proxy now if we don't have one
7023 // and initialize it later in CreateNewGlobals.
7024 DirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> global_proxy;
7025 if (!maybe_global_proxy.ToHandle(&global_proxy)) {
7026 int instance_size = 0;
7027 if (context_snapshot_index > 0) {
7028 // The global proxy function to reinitialize this global proxy is in the
7029 // context that is yet to be deserialized. We need to prepare a global
7030 // proxy of the correct size.
7031 Tagged<Object> size =
7032 isolate->heap()->serialized_global_proxy_sizes()->get(
7033 static_cast<int>(context_snapshot_index) -
7034 SnapshotCreatorImpl::kFirstAddtlContextIndex);
7035 instance_size = Smi::ToInt(size);
7036 } else {
7037 instance_size = JSGlobalProxy::SizeWithEmbedderFields(
7038 global_proxy_template.IsEmpty()
7039 ? 0
7040 : global_proxy_template->InternalFieldCount());
7041 }
7042 global_proxy =
7043 isolate->factory()->NewUninitializedJSGlobalProxy(instance_size);
7044 }
7045
7046 // We can only de-serialize a context if the isolate was initialized from
7047 // a snapshot. Otherwise we have to build the context from scratch.
7048 // Also create a context from scratch to expose natives, if required by flag.
7049 DCHECK(native_context_.is_null());
7050 if (isolate->initialized_from_snapshot()) {
7051 DirectHandle<Context> context;
7052 if (Snapshot::NewContextFromSnapshot(isolate, global_proxy,
7053 context_snapshot_index,
7054 embedder_fields_deserializer)
7055 .ToHandle(&context)) {
7056 native_context_ = Cast<NativeContext>(context);
7057 }
7058 }
7059
7060 if (!native_context().is_null()) {
7061 AddToWeakNativeContextList(isolate, *native_context());
7062 isolate->set_context(*native_context());
7063
7064 // If no global proxy template was passed in, simply use the global in the
7065 // snapshot. If a global proxy template was passed in it's used to recreate
7066 // the global object and its prototype chain, and the data and the accessor
7067 // properties from the deserialized global are copied onto it.
7068 if (context_snapshot_index == 0 && !global_proxy_template.IsEmpty()) {
7069 DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> global_object =
7070 CreateNewGlobals(global_proxy_template, global_proxy);
7071 HookUpGlobalObject(global_object);
7072 if (!ConfigureGlobalObject(global_proxy_template)) return;
7073 } else {
7074 // The global proxy needs to be integrated into the native context.
7075 HookUpGlobalProxy(global_proxy);
7076 }
7077 DCHECK_EQ(global_proxy->GetCreationContext(), *native_context());
7078 DCHECK(!global_proxy->IsDetachedFrom(native_context()->global_object()));
7079 } else {
7080 DCHECK(native_context().is_null());
7081
7082 Isolate::EnableRoAllocationForSnapshotScope enable_ro_allocation(isolate);
7083
7084 base::ElapsedTimer timer;
7085 if (v8_flags.profile_deserialization) timer.Start();
7086 DCHECK_EQ(0u, context_snapshot_index);
7087 // We get here if there was no context snapshot.
7088 CreateRoots();
7089 MathRandom::InitializeContext(isolate, native_context());
7090 DirectHandle<JSFunction> empty_function = CreateEmptyFunction();
7091 CreateSloppyModeFunctionMaps(empty_function);
7092 CreateStrictModeFunctionMaps(empty_function);
7093 CreateObjectFunction(empty_function);
7094 CreateIteratorMaps(empty_function);
7095 CreateAsyncIteratorMaps(empty_function);
7096 CreateAsyncFunctionMaps(empty_function);
7097 DirectHandle<JSGlobalObject> global_object =
7098 CreateNewGlobals(global_proxy_template, global_proxy);
7099 InitializeMapCaches();
7100 InitializeGlobal(global_object, empty_function);
7101 InitializeIteratorFunctions();
7102 InitializeCallSiteBuiltins();
7103
7104 if (!InstallABunchOfRandomThings()) return;
7105 if (!InstallExtrasBindings()) return;
7106 if (!ConfigureGlobalObject(global_proxy_template)) return;
7107
7108#ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
7109 WasmJs::PrepareForSnapshot(isolate);
7110#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
7111
7112 if (v8_flags.profile_deserialization) {
7113 double ms = timer.Elapsed().InMillisecondsF();
7114 PrintF("[Initializing context from scratch took %0.3f ms]\n", ms);
7115 }
7116 }
7117
7118 native_context()->set_microtask_queue(
7119 isolate, microtask_queue ? static_cast<MicrotaskQueue*>(microtask_queue)
7120 : isolate->default_microtask_queue());
7121
7122 // Install experimental natives. Do not include them into the
7123 // snapshot as we should be able to turn them off at runtime. Re-installing
7124 // them after they have already been deserialized would also fail.
7125 if (!isolate->serializer_enabled()) {
7126 InitializeExperimentalGlobal();
7127
7128 // Store String.prototype's map again in case it has been changed by
7129 // experimental natives.
7130 DirectHandle<JSFunction> string_function(
7131 native_context()->string_function(), isolate);
7132 Tagged<JSObject> string_function_prototype =
7133 Cast<JSObject>(string_function->initial_map()->prototype());
7134 DCHECK(string_function_prototype->HasFastProperties());
7135 native_context()->set_string_function_prototype_map(
7136 string_function_prototype->map());
7137 }
7138
7139 if (v8_flags.disallow_code_generation_from_strings) {
7140 native_context()->set_allow_code_gen_from_strings(
7141 ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).false_value());
7142 }
7143
7144 // We created new functions, which may require debug instrumentation.
7145 if (isolate->debug()->is_active()) {
7146 isolate->debug()->InstallDebugBreakTrampoline();
7147 }
7148
7149 native_context()->ResetErrorsThrown();
7150 result_ = native_context();
7151}
7152
7153Genesis::Genesis(Isolate* isolate,
7154 MaybeDirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> maybe_global_proxy,
7155 v8::Local<v8::ObjectTemplate> global_proxy_template)
7156 : isolate_(isolate), active_(isolate->bootstrapper()) {
7157 result_ = {};
7158 global_proxy_ = {};
7159
7160 // Before creating the roots we must save the context and restore it
7161 // on all function exits.
7162 SaveContext saved_context(isolate);
7163
7164 const int proxy_size = JSGlobalProxy::SizeWithEmbedderFields(
7165 global_proxy_template->InternalFieldCount());
7166
7167 DirectHandle<JSGlobalProxy> global_proxy;
7168 if (maybe_global_proxy.ToHandle(&global_proxy)) {
7169 global_proxy->map()->set_map(isolate, ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).meta_map());
7170 } else {
7171 global_proxy = factory()->NewUninitializedJSGlobalProxy(proxy_size);
7172 }
7173
7174 // Create a remote object as the global object.
7175 DirectHandle<ObjectTemplateInfo> global_proxy_data =
7176 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*global_proxy_template);
7177 DirectHandle<FunctionTemplateInfo> global_constructor(
7178 Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(global_proxy_data->constructor()), isolate);
7179
7180 DirectHandle<ObjectTemplateInfo> global_object_template(
7181 Cast<ObjectTemplateInfo>(global_constructor->GetPrototypeTemplate()),
7182 isolate);
7183 DirectHandle<JSObject> global_object =
7184 ApiNatives::InstantiateRemoteObject(global_object_template)
7185 .ToHandleChecked();
7186
7187 // (Re)initialize the global proxy object.
7188 DCHECK_EQ(global_proxy_data->embedder_field_count(),
7189 global_proxy_template->InternalFieldCount());
7190 DirectHandle<Map> global_proxy_map = factory()->NewContextlessMap(
7191 JS_GLOBAL_PROXY_TYPE, proxy_size, TERMINAL_FAST_ELEMENTS_KIND);
7192 global_proxy_map->set_is_access_check_needed(true);
7193 global_proxy_map->set_may_have_interesting_properties(true);
7194
7195 // Configure the hidden prototype chain of the global proxy.
7196 JSObject::ForceSetPrototype(isolate, global_proxy, global_object);
7197 global_proxy->map()->SetConstructor(*global_constructor);
7198
7199 global_proxy_ = global_proxy;
7200}
7201
7202// Support for thread preemption.
7203
7204// Reserve space for statics needing saving and restoring.
7205int Bootstrapper::ArchiveSpacePerThread() { return sizeof(NestingCounterType); }
7206
7207// Archive statics that are thread-local.
7208char* Bootstrapper::ArchiveState(char* to) {
7209 *reinterpret_cast<NestingCounterType*>(to) = nesting_;
7210 nesting_ = 0;
7211 return to + sizeof(NestingCounterType);
7212}
7213
7214// Restore statics that are thread-local.
7215char* Bootstrapper::RestoreState(char* from) {
7216 nesting_ = *reinterpret_cast<NestingCounterType*>(from);
7217 return from + sizeof(NestingCounterType);
7218}
7219
7220// Called when the top-level V8 mutex is destroyed.
7221void Bootstrapper::FreeThreadResources() { DCHECK(!IsActive()); }
7222
7223} // namespace internal
7224} // namespace v8
